77//---------------------------------------------------------------------------

79// replaces { with < and } with > and also
80// replaces &gt; with < and &gt; with > within string s
81static void unescapeCRef(QCString &s)
82{
83 QCString result;
84 const char *p = s.data();
85 if (p)
86 {
87 char c = 0;
88 while ((c=*p++))
89 {
90 if (c=='{') c='<'; else if (c=='}') c='>';
91 result+=c;
92 }
93 }
94
95 result=substitute(result,"&lt;","<");
96 result=substitute(result,"&gt;",">");
97 s = result;
98}

100//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
101
102/*! Strips known html and tex extensions from \a text. */
103static QCString stripKnownExtensions(const QCString &text)
104{
105 QCString result=text;
106 if (result.endsWith(".tex"))
107 {
108 result=result.left(result.length()-4);
109 }
110 else if (result.right(Doxygen::htmlFileExtension.length())==
111 QCString(Doxygen::htmlFileExtension))
112 {
113 result=result.left(result.length()-Doxygen::htmlFileExtension.length());
114 }
115 return result;
116}
117
118static void setParent(DocNodeVariant *n,DocNodeVariant *newParent)
119{
120 std::visit([&](auto &&x)->decltype(auto) { return x.setParent(newParent); }, *n);
121}

123//----------- DocStyleChange
124
125const char *DocStyleChange::styleString() const
126{
127 switch (m_style)
128 {
129 case DocStyleChange::Bold: return "b";
130 case DocStyleChange::Italic: return "em";
131 case DocStyleChange::Code: return "code";
132 case DocStyleChange::Center: return "center";
133 case DocStyleChange::Small: return "small";
134 case DocStyleChange::Cite: return "cite";
135 case DocStyleChange::Subscript: return "subscript";
136 case DocStyleChange::Superscript: return "superscript";
137 case DocStyleChange::Preformatted: return "pre";
138 case DocStyleChange::Div: return "div";
139 case DocStyleChange::Span: return "span";
140 case DocStyleChange::Strike: return "strike";
141 case DocStyleChange::S: return "s";
142 case DocStyleChange::Del: return "del";
143 case DocStyleChange::Underline: return "u";
144 case DocStyleChange::Ins: return "ins";
145 }
146 return "<invalid>";
147}

156//----------- DocEmoji
157
158DocEmoji::DocEmoji(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &symName) :
159 DocNode(parser,parent), m_symName(symName), m_index(-1)
160{
161 QCString locSymName = symName;
162 size_t len=locSymName.length();
163 if (len>0)
164 {
165 if (locSymName.at(len-1)!=':') locSymName.append(":");
166 if (locSymName.at(0)!=':') locSymName.prepend(":");
167 }
168 m_symName = locSymName;
169 m_index = EmojiEntityMapper::instance().symbol2index(m_symName.str());
170 if (m_index==-1)
171 {
172 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Found unsupported emoji symbol '%s'",qPrint(m_symName));
173 }
174}

205//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
206
207DocAnchor::DocAnchor(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &id,bool newAnchor) : DocNode(parser,parent)
208{
209 if (id.isEmpty())
210 {
211 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Empty anchor label");
212 return;
213 }
214
215 const CitationManager &ct = CitationManager::instance();
216 QCString anchorPrefix = ct.anchorPrefix();
217 if (id.left(anchorPrefix.length()) == anchorPrefix)
218 {
219 const CiteInfo *cite = ct.find(id.mid(anchorPrefix.length()));
220 if (cite)
221 {
222 m_file = convertNameToFile(ct.fileName(),FALSE,TRUE);
223 m_anchor = id;
224 }
225 else
226 {
227 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Invalid cite anchor id '%s'",qPrint(id));
228 m_anchor = "invalid";
229 m_file = "invalid";
230 }
231 }
232 else if (newAnchor) // found <a name="label">
233 {
234 m_anchor = id;
235 }
236 else // found \anchor label
237 {
238 const SectionInfo *sec = SectionManager::instance().find(id);
239 if (sec)
240 {
241 //printf("Found anchor %s\n",qPrint(id));
242 m_file = sec->fileName();
243 m_anchor = sec->label();
244 }
245 else
246 {
247 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Invalid anchor id '%s'",qPrint(id));
248 m_anchor = "invalid";
249 m_file = "invalid";
250 }
251 }
252}

260{
261}

264//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
265
266void DocInclude::parse()
267{
268 AUTO_TRACE("file={} text={}",m_file,Trace::trunc(m_text));
269 switch(m_type)
270 {
271 case DontIncWithLines:
272 // fall through
273 case IncWithLines:
274 // fall through
275 case Include:
276 // fall through
277 case DontInclude:
278 parser()->readTextFileByName(m_file,m_text);
279 parser()->context.includeFileName = m_file;
280 parser()->context.includeFileText = m_text;
281 parser()->context.includeFileOffset = 0;
282 parser()->context.includeFileLength = m_text.length();
283 parser()->context.includeFileLine = 0;
284 parser()->context.includeFileShowLineNo = (m_type == DontIncWithLines || m_type == IncWithLines);
285 parser()->context.stripCodeComments = m_stripCodeComments;
286 //printf("parser->context.includeFile=<<%s>>\n",qPrint(parser->context.includeFileText));
287 break;
288 case VerbInclude:
289 // fall through
290 case HtmlInclude:
291 case LatexInclude:
292 case DocInclude::RtfInclude:
293 case DocInclude::ManInclude:
294 case DocInclude::XmlInclude:
295 case DocInclude::DocbookInclude:
296 parser()->readTextFileByName(m_file,m_text);
297 break;
298 case Snippet:
299 case SnippetWithLines:
300 parser()->readTextFileByName(m_file,m_text);
301 // check here for the existence of the blockId inside the file, so we
302 // only generate the warning once.
303 int count = 0;
304 if (!m_blockId.isEmpty() && (count=m_text.contains(m_blockId.data()))!=2)
305 {
306 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,
307 parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),
308 "block marked with %s for \\snippet should appear twice in file %s, found it %d times",
309 qPrint(m_blockId),qPrint(m_file),count);
310 }
311 break;
312 }
313}
314
315//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
316
317void DocIncOperator::parse()
318{
319 if (parser()->context.includeFileName.isEmpty())
320 {
321 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),
322 "No previous '\\include' or '\\dontinclude' command for '\\%s' present",
323 typeAsString());
324 }
325 bool found = false;
326
327 m_includeFileName = parser()->context.includeFileName;
328 const char *p = parser()->context.includeFileText.data();
329 size_t l = parser()->context.includeFileLength;
330 size_t o = parser()->context.includeFileOffset;
331 int il = parser()->context.includeFileLine;
332 AUTO_TRACE("text={} off={} len={}",Trace::trunc(p),o,l);
333 size_t so = o, bo = 0;
334 bool nonEmpty = FALSE;
335 switch(type())
336 {
337 case Line:
338 while (o<l)
339 {
340 char c = p[o];
341 if (c=='\n')
342 {
343 parser()->context.includeFileLine++;
344 if (nonEmpty) break; // we have a pattern to match
345 so=o+1; // no pattern, skip empty line
346 }
347 else if (!isspace(static_cast<uint8_t>(c))) // no white space char
348 {
349 nonEmpty=TRUE;
350 }
351 o++;
352 }
353 if (parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so).find(m_pattern)!=-1)
354 {
355 m_line = il;
356 m_text = parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so);
357 found = true;
358 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("\\line {}",Trace::trunc(m_text));
359 }
360 parser()->context.includeFileOffset = std::min(l,o+1); // set pointer to start of new line
361 m_showLineNo = parser()->context.includeFileShowLineNo;
362 m_stripCodeComments = parser()->context.stripCodeComments;
363 break;
364 case SkipLine:
365 while (o<l)
366 {
367 so=o;
368 while (o<l)
369 {
370 char c = p[o];
371 if (c=='\n')
372 {
373 parser()->context.includeFileLine++;
374 if (nonEmpty) break; // we have a pattern to match
375 so=o+1; // no pattern, skip empty line
376 }
377 else if (!isspace(static_cast<uint8_t>(c))) // no white space char
378 {
379 nonEmpty=TRUE;
380 }
381 o++;
382 }
383 if (parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so).find(m_pattern)!=-1)
384 {
385 m_line = il;
386 m_text = parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so);
387 found = true;
388 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("\\skipline {}",Trace::trunc(m_text));
389 break;
390 }
391 o++; // skip new line
392 }
393 parser()->context.includeFileOffset = std::min(l,o+1); // set pointer to start of new line
394 m_showLineNo = parser()->context.includeFileShowLineNo;
395 m_stripCodeComments = parser()->context.stripCodeComments;
396 break;
397 case Skip:
398 while (o<l)
399 {
400 so=o;
401 while (o<l)
402 {
403 char c = p[o];
404 if (c=='\n')
405 {
406 parser()->context.includeFileLine++;
407 if (nonEmpty) break; // we have a pattern to match
408 so=o+1; // no pattern, skip empty line
409 }
410 else if (!isspace(static_cast<uint8_t>(c))) // no white space char
411 {
412 nonEmpty=TRUE;
413 }
414 o++;
415 }
416 if (parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so).find(m_pattern)!=-1)
417 {
418 found = true;
419 break;
420 }
421 o++; // skip new line
422 }
423 parser()->context.includeFileOffset = so; // set pointer to start of new line
424 m_showLineNo = parser()->context.includeFileShowLineNo;
425 m_stripCodeComments = parser()->context.stripCodeComments;
426 break;
427 case Until:
428 bo=o;
429 while (o<l)
430 {
431 so=o;
432 while (o<l)
433 {
434 char c = p[o];
435 if (c=='\n')
436 {
437 parser()->context.includeFileLine++;
438 if (nonEmpty) break; // we have a pattern to match
439 so=o+1; // no pattern, skip empty line
440 }
441 else if (!isspace(static_cast<uint8_t>(c))) // no white space char
442 {
443 nonEmpty=TRUE;
444 }
445 o++;
446 }
447 if (parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(so,o-so).find(m_pattern)!=-1)
448 {
449 m_line = il;
450 m_text = parser()->context.includeFileText.mid(bo,o-bo);
451 found = true;
452 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("\\until {}",Trace::trunc(m_text));
453 break;
454 }
455 o++; // skip new line
456 }
457 parser()->context.includeFileOffset = std::min(l,o+1); // set pointer to start of new line
458 m_showLineNo = parser()->context.includeFileShowLineNo;
459 m_stripCodeComments = parser()->context.stripCodeComments;
460 break;
461 }
462 if (!found)
463 {
464 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),
465 "referenced pattern '%s' for command '\\%s' not found",qPrint(m_pattern),typeAsString());
466 }
467}

469//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
470
471DocXRefItem::DocXRefItem(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,int id,const QCString &key) :
472 DocCompoundNode(parser,parent), m_id(id), m_key(key), m_relPath(parser->context.relPath)
473{
474}
475
476bool DocXRefItem::parse()
477{
478 RefList *refList = RefListManager::instance().find(m_key);
479 if (refList && refList->isEnabled())
480 {
481 RefItem *item = refList->find(m_id);
482 ASSERT(item!=nullptr);
483 if (item)
484 {
485 if (parser()->context.memberDef && parser()->context.memberDef->name().at(0)=='@')
486 {
487 m_file = "@"; // can't cross reference anonymous enum
488 m_anchor = "@";
489 }
490 else
491 {
492 m_file = refList->fileName();
493 m_anchor = item->anchor();
494 }
495 m_title = refList->sectionTitle();
496 //printf("DocXRefItem: file=%s anchor=%s title=%s\n",
497 // qPrint(m_file),qPrint(m_anchor),qPrint(m_title));
498
499 if (!item->text().isEmpty())
500 {
501 parser()->pushContext();
502 parser()->internalValidatingParseDoc(thisVariant(),children(),item->text());
503 parser()->popContext();
504 }
505 }
506 return TRUE;
507 }
508 return FALSE;
509}
510
511//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
512
513DocFormula::DocFormula(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,int id) : DocNode(parser,parent),
514 m_relPath(parser->context.relPath)
515{
516 const Formula *formula = FormulaManager::instance().findFormula(id);
517 if (formula && !formula->text().isEmpty())
518 {
519 m_id = id;
520 m_name.sprintf("form_%d",m_id);
521 m_text = formula->text();
522 }
523 else // wrong \_form#<n> command
524 {
525 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Wrong formula id %d",id);
526 m_id = -1;
527 }
528}

530//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
531
532DocSecRefItem::DocSecRefItem(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &target) :
533 DocCompoundNode(parser,parent), m_target(target), m_relPath(parser->context.relPath)
534{
535}
536
537void DocSecRefItem::parse()
538{
539 AUTO_TRACE();
540 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
541
542 parser()->tokenizer.setStateTitle();
543 Token tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
544 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
545 {
546 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children()))
547 {
548 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant(),tok,children(),"\\refitem");
549 }
550 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
551 }
552 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
553 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant(),children());
554
555 if (!m_target.isEmpty())
556 {
557 const SectionInfo *sec = SectionManager::instance().find(m_target);
558 if (sec==nullptr && parser()->context.lang==SrcLangExt::Markdown) // lookup as markdown file
559 {
560 sec = SectionManager::instance().find(markdownFileNameToId(m_target));
561 }
562 if (sec) // ref to section or anchor
563 {
564 // set defaults
565 m_ref = sec->ref();
566 m_file = stripKnownExtensions(sec->fileName());
567 m_refType = Section;
568 m_anchor = sec->label();
569 m_isSubPage = false;
570 // adjust if needed
571 switch (sec->type().level())
572 {
573 case SectionType::Page:
574 {
575 PageDef *pd = Doxygen::pageLinkedMap->find(m_target);
576 m_isSubPage = pd && pd->hasParentPage();
577 if (!m_isSubPage)
578 {
579 m_anchor="";
580 }
581 }
582 break;
583 case SectionType::Anchor:
584 m_refType = Anchor;
585 break;
586 case SectionType::Table:
587 m_refType = Table;
588 break;
589 default:
590 break;
591 }
592 //printf("m_ref=%s,m_file=%s,type=%d\n",
593 // qPrint(m_ref),qPrint(m_file),m_refType);
594 }
595 else
596 {
597 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"reference to unknown section %s",
598 qPrint(m_target));
599 }
600 }
601 else
602 {
603 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"reference to empty target");
604 }
605}
606
607//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
608
609void DocSecRefList::parse()
610{
611 AUTO_TRACE();
612 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
613
614 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
615 // skip white space
616 while (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE, TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA)) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
617 // handle items
618 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
619 {
620 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_COMMAND_AT, TokenRetval::TK_COMMAND_BS))
621 {
622 switch (Mappers::cmdMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name))
623 {
624 case CommandType::CMD_SECREFITEM:
625 {
626 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
627 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
628 {
629 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\refitem command");
630 break;
631 }
632 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
633 if (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WORD,TokenRetval::TK_LNKWORD))
634 {
635 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of \\refitem",
636 tok.to_string());
637 break;
638 }
639
640 children().append<DocSecRefItem>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->name);
641 children().get_last<DocSecRefItem>()->parse();
642 }
643 break;
644 case CommandType::CMD_ENDSECREFLIST:
645 return;
646 default:
647 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Illegal command '%c%s' as part of a \\secreflist",
648 tok.command_to_char(),qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
649 return;
650 }
651 }
652 else if (tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
653 {
654 // ignore whitespace
655 }
656 else
657 {
658 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected token %s inside section reference list",
659 tok.to_string());
660 return;
661 }
662 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
663 }
664
665}
666
667//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
668
669DocInternalRef::DocInternalRef(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &ref)
670 : DocCompoundNode(parser,parent), m_relPath(parser->context.relPath)
671{
672 int i=ref.find('#');
673 if (i!=-1)
674 {
675 m_anchor = ref.right(static_cast<int>(ref.length())-i-1);
676 m_file = ref.left(i);
677 }
678 else
679 {
680 m_file = ref;
681 }
682}
683
684void DocInternalRef::parse()
685{
686 AUTO_TRACE();
687 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
688
689 Token tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
690 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
691 {
692 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children()))
693 {
694 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant(),tok,children(),"\\ref");
695 }
696 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
697 }
698
699 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant(),children());
700}
701
702//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
703
704DocRef::DocRef(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &target,const QCString &context) :
705 DocCompoundNode(parser,parent), m_refType(Unknown), m_isSubPage(FALSE)
706{
707 const Definition *compound = nullptr;
708 QCString anchor;
709 //printf("DocRef::DocRef(target=%s,context=%s)\n",qPrint(target),qPrint(context));
710 ASSERT(!target.isEmpty());
711 m_relPath = parser->context.relPath;
712 const SectionInfo *sec = SectionManager::instance().find(parser->context.prefix+target);
713 if (sec==nullptr && getLanguageFromFileName(target)==SrcLangExt::Markdown) // lookup as markdown file
714 {
715 sec = SectionManager::instance().find(markdownFileNameToId(target));
716 }
717 if (sec) // ref to section or anchor
718 {
719 PageDef *pd = nullptr;
720 int secLevel = sec->type().level();
721 if (secLevel==SectionType::Page)
722 {
723 pd = Doxygen::pageLinkedMap->find(target);
724 }
725 m_text = sec->title();
726 if (m_text.isEmpty()) m_text = sec->label();
727
728 m_ref = sec->ref();
729 m_file = stripKnownExtensions(sec->fileName());
730 if (secLevel==SectionType::Anchor)
731 {
732 m_refType = Anchor;
733 }
734 else if (secLevel==SectionType::Table)
735 {
736 m_refType = Table;
737 }
738 else
739 {
740 m_refType = Section;
741 }
742 m_isSubPage = pd && pd->hasParentPage();
743 if (secLevel!=SectionType::Page || m_isSubPage) m_anchor = sec->label();
744 m_sectionType = sec->type();
745 //printf("m_text=%s,m_ref=%s,m_file=%s,type=%d\n",
746 // qPrint(m_text),qPrint(m_ref),qPrint(m_file),m_refType);
747 return;
748 }
749 else if (resolveLink(context,target,true,&compound,anchor,parser->context.prefix))
750 {
751 bool isFile = compound ?
752 (compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypeFile ||
753 compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypePage ? TRUE : FALSE) :
754 FALSE;
755 m_text = linkToText(parser->context.lang,target,isFile);
756 m_anchor = anchor;
757 if (compound && compound->isLinkable()) // ref to compound
758 {
759 if (anchor.isEmpty() && /* compound link */
760 compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypeGroup && /* is group */
761 !toGroupDef(compound)->groupTitle().isEmpty() /* with title */
762 )
763 {
764 m_text=(toGroupDef(compound))->groupTitle(); // use group's title as link
765 }
766 else if (compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember &&
767 toMemberDef(compound)->isObjCMethod())
768 {
769 // Objective C Method
770 const MemberDef *member = toMemberDef(compound);
771 bool localLink = parser->context.memberDef ? member->getClassDef()==parser->context.memberDef->getClassDef() : FALSE;
772 m_text = member->objCMethodName(localLink,parser->context.inSeeBlock);
773 }
774 else if (Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES))
775 {
776 m_text=stripScope(m_text);
777 }
778
779 m_file = compound->getOutputFileBase();
780 m_ref = compound->getReference();
781 //printf("isFile=%d compound=%s (%d)\n",isFile,qPrint(compound->name()),
782 // compound->definitionType());
783 return;
784 }
785 else if (compound && compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypeFile &&
786 toFileDef(compound)->generateSourceFile()
787 ) // undocumented file that has source code we can link to
788 {
789 m_file = compound->getSourceFileBase();
790 m_ref = compound->getReference();
791 return;
792 }
793 }
794 m_text = target;
795 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unable to resolve reference to '%s' for \\ref command",
796 qPrint(target));
797}
798
799void DocNodeList::move_append(DocNodeList &elements)
800{
801 for (auto &&elem : elements)
802 {
803 emplace_back(std::move(elem));
804 }
805 elements.clear();
806}
807
808static void flattenParagraphs(DocNodeVariant *root,DocNodeList &children)
809{
810 DocNodeList newChildren;
811 for (auto &dn : children)
812 {
813 DocPara *para = std::get_if<DocPara>(&dn);
814 if (para)
815 {
816 //// move the children of the paragraph to the end of the newChildren list
817 newChildren.move_append(para->children());
818 }
819 }
820
821 // replace the children list by the newChildren list
822 children.clear();
823 children.move_append(newChildren);
824 // reparent the children
825 for (auto &cn : children)
826 {
827 setParent(&cn,root);
828 // we also need to set the parent for each child of cn, as cn's address may have changed.
829 auto opt_children = call_method_children(&cn);
830 if (opt_children)
831 {
832 for (auto &ccn : *opt_children)
833 {
834 setParent(&ccn,&cn);
835 }
836 }
837 }
838}
839
840void DocRef::parse()
841{
842 AUTO_TRACE();
843 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
844
845 Token tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
846 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
847 {
848 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children()))
849 {
850 switch (tok.value())
851 {
852 case TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG:
853 break;
854 default:
855 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant(),tok,children(),"\\ref");
856 break;
857 }
858 }
859 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
860 }
861
862 if (children().empty() && !m_text.isEmpty())
863 {
864 QCString text = m_text;
865 if (parser()->context.insideHtmlLink)
866 {
867 // we already in a link/title only output anchor
868 text = m_anchor;
869 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),
870 "Potential recursion while resolving \\ref command!");
871 }
872 parser()->context.insideHtmlLink=TRUE;
873 parser()->pushContext();
874 parser()->internalValidatingParseDoc(thisVariant(),children(),text);
875 parser()->popContext();
876 parser()->context.insideHtmlLink=FALSE;
877 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
878 flattenParagraphs(thisVariant(),children());
879 }
880
881 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant(),children());
882}
883
884//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
885
886DocCite::DocCite(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &target,const QCString &) : DocNode(parser,parent)
887{
888 size_t numBibFiles = Config_getList(CITE_BIB_FILES).size();
889 //printf("DocCite::DocCite(target=%s)\n",qPrint(target));
890 ASSERT(!target.isEmpty());
891 m_relPath = parser->context.relPath;
892 const CitationManager &ct = CitationManager::instance();
893 const CiteInfo *cite = ct.find(target);
894 //printf("cite=%p text='%s' numBibFiles=%d\n",cite,cite?qPrint(cite->text):"<null>",numBibFiles);
895 if (numBibFiles>0 && cite && !cite->text().isEmpty()) // ref to citation
896 {
897 m_text = cite->text();
898 m_ref = "";
899 m_anchor = ct.anchorPrefix()+cite->label();
900 m_file = convertNameToFile(ct.fileName(),FALSE,TRUE);
901 //printf("CITE ==> m_text=%s,m_ref=%s,m_file=%s,m_anchor=%s\n",
902 // qPrint(m_text),qPrint(m_ref),qPrint(m_file),qPrint(m_anchor));
903 return;
904 }
905 m_text = target;
906 if (numBibFiles==0)
907 {
908 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"\\cite command found but no bib files specified via CITE_BIB_FILES!");
909 }
910 else if (cite==nullptr)
911 {
912 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unable to resolve reference to '%s' for \\cite command",
913 qPrint(target));
914 }
915 else
916 {
917 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"\\cite command to '%s' does not have an associated number",
918 qPrint(target));
919 }
920}
921
922//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
923
924DocLink::DocLink(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &target) : DocCompoundNode(parser,parent)
925{
926 const Definition *compound = nullptr;
927 QCString anchor;
928 m_refText = target;
929 m_relPath = parser->context.relPath;
930 if (!m_refText.isEmpty() && m_refText.at(0)=='#')
931 {
932 m_refText = m_refText.right(m_refText.length()-1);
933 }
934 if (resolveLink(parser->context.context,stripKnownExtensions(target),parser->context.inSeeBlock,&compound,anchor,parser->context.prefix))
935 {
936 m_anchor = anchor;
937 if (compound && compound->isLinkable())
938 {
939 m_file = compound->getOutputFileBase();
940 m_ref = compound->getReference();
941 }
942 else if (compound && compound->definitionType()==Definition::TypeFile &&
943 (toFileDef(compound))->generateSourceFile()
944 ) // undocumented file that has source code we can link to
945 {
946 m_file = compound->getSourceFileBase();
947 m_ref = compound->getReference();
948 }
949 return;
950 }
951
952 // bogus link target
953 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unable to resolve link to '%s' for \\link command",
954 qPrint(target));
955}
956
957
958QCString DocLink::parse(bool isJavaLink,bool isXmlLink)
959{
960 AUTO_TRACE();
961 QCString result;
962 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
963
964 Token tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
965 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
966 {
967 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children(),FALSE))
968 {
969 switch (tok.value())
970 {
971 case TokenRetval::TK_COMMAND_AT:
972 // fall through
973 case TokenRetval::TK_COMMAND_BS:
974 switch (Mappers::cmdMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name))
975 {
976 case CommandType::CMD_ENDLINK:
977 if (isJavaLink)
978 {
979 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"'{@link...' ended with '%c%s' command",
980 tok.command_to_char(),qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
981 }
982 goto endlink;
983 default:
984 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Illegal command '%c%s' as part of a \\link",
985 tok.command_to_char(),qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
986 break;
987 }
988 break;
989 case TokenRetval::TK_SYMBOL:
990 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unsupported symbol '%s' found as part of a \\link",
991 qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
992 break;
993 case TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG:
994 if (parser()->context.token->name!="see" || !isXmlLink)
995 {
996 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected xml/html command %s found as part of a \\link",
997 qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
998 }
999 goto endlink;
1000 case TokenRetval::TK_LNKWORD:
1001 case TokenRetval::TK_WORD:
1002 if (isJavaLink) // special case to detect closing }
1003 {
1004 QCString w = parser()->context.token->name;
1005 int p = 0;
1006 if (w=="}")
1007 {
1008 goto endlink;
1009 }
1010 else if ((p=w.find('}'))!=-1)
1011 {
1012 int l = static_cast<int>(w.length());
1013 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant(),w.left(p));
1014 if (p<l-1) // something left after the } (for instance a .)
1015 {
1016 result=w.right(l-p-1);
1017 }
1018 goto endlink;
1019 }
1020 }
1021 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->name);
1022 break;
1023 default:
1024 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected token %s",tok.to_string());
1025 break;
1026 }
1027 }
1028 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1029 }
1030 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1031 {
1032 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,
1033 parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),
1034 "Unexpected end of comment while inside link command");
1035 }
1036endlink:
1037
1038 if (children().empty()) // no link text
1039 {
1040 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant(),m_refText);
1041 }
1042
1043 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant(),children());
1044 return result;
1045}

1050DocDotFile::DocDotFile(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &name,const QCString &context,

1055}
1056
1057bool DocDotFile::parse()
1058{
1059 bool ok = false;
1060 parser()->defaultHandleTitleAndSize(CommandType::CMD_DOTFILE,thisVariant(),children(),p->width,p->height);
1061
1062 bool ambig = false;
1063 FileDef *fd = findFileDef(Doxygen::dotFileNameLinkedMap,p->name,ambig);
1064 if (fd==nullptr && !p->name.endsWith(".dot")) // try with .dot extension as well
1065 {
1066 fd = findFileDef(Doxygen::dotFileNameLinkedMap,p->name+".dot",ambig);
1067 }
1068 if (fd)
1069 {
1070 p->file = fd->absFilePath();
1071 ok = true;
1072 if (ambig)
1073 {
1074 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"included dot file name '%s' is ambiguous.\n"
1075 "Possible candidates:\n%s",qPrint(p->name),
1076 qPrint(showFileDefMatches(Doxygen::dotFileNameLinkedMap,p->name))
1077 );
1078 }
1079 }
1080 else
1081 {
1082 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"included dot file '%s' is not found "
1083 "in any of the paths specified via DOTFILE_DIRS!",qPrint(p->name));
1084 }
1085 return ok;
1086}

1214
1215void DocVhdlFlow::parse()
1216{
1217 AUTO_TRACE();
1218 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1219
1220 parser()->tokenizer.setStateTitle();
1221 Token tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1222 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1223 {
1224 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children()))
1225 {
1226 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant(),tok,children(),"\\vhdlflow");
1227 }
1228 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1229 }
1230 parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1231
1232 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
1233 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant(),children());
1234
1235 VhdlDocGen::createFlowChart(parser()->context.memberDef);
1236}

1240
1241DocImage::DocImage(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const HtmlAttribList &attribs,const QCString &name,
1242 Type t,const QCString &url, bool inlineImage) :
1243 DocCompoundNode(parser,parent), p(std::make_unique<Private>(attribs, name, t, parser->context.relPath, url, inlineImage))
1244{
1245}
1246
1247bool DocImage::isSVG() const
1248{
1249 QCString locName = p->url.isEmpty() ? p->name : p->url;
1250 int len = static_cast<int>(locName.length());
1251 int fnd = locName.find('?'); // ignore part from ? until end
1252 if (fnd==-1) fnd=len;
1253 return fnd>=4 && locName.mid(fnd-4,4)==".svg";
1254}
1255
1256void DocImage::parse()
1257{
1258 parser()->defaultHandleTitleAndSize(CommandType::CMD_IMAGE,thisVariant(),children(),p->width,p->height);
1259}

1261
1262//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1263
1264Token DocHtmlHeader::parse()
1265{
1266 AUTO_TRACE();
1267 Token retval(TokenRetval::RetVal_OK);
1268 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1269
1270 Token tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1271 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1272 {
1273 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children()))
1274 {
1275 switch (tok.value())
1276 {
1277 case TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG:
1278 {
1279 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1280 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_H1 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h1> tag
1281 {
1282 if (m_level!=1)
1283 {
1284 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h1>",
1285 m_level);
1286 }
1287 goto endheader;
1288 }
1289 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_H2 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h2> tag
1290 {
1291 if (m_level!=2)
1292 {
1293 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h2>",
1294 m_level);
1295 }
1296 goto endheader;
1297 }
1298 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_H3 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h3> tag
1299 {
1300 if (m_level!=3)
1301 {
1302 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h3>",
1303 m_level);
1304 }
1305 goto endheader;
1306 }
1307 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_H4 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h4> tag
1308 {
1309 if (m_level!=4)
1310 {
1311 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h4>",
1312 m_level);
1313 }
1314 goto endheader;
1315 }
1316 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_H5 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h5> tag
1317 {
1318 if (m_level!=5)
1319 {
1320 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h5>",
1321 m_level);
1322 }
1323 goto endheader;
1324 }
1325 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_H6 && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </h6> tag
1326 {
1327 if (m_level!=6)
1328 {
1329 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"<h%d> ended with </h6>",
1330 m_level);
1331 }
1332 goto endheader;
1333 }
1334 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_A)
1335 {
1336 if (!parser()->context.token->endTag)
1337 {
1338 parser()->handleAHref(thisVariant(),children(),parser()->context.token->attribs);
1339 }
1340 }
1341 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_BR)
1342 {
1343 children().append<DocLineBreak>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->attribs);
1344 }
1345 else
1346 {
1347 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected html tag <%s%s> found within <h%d> context",
1348 parser()->context.token->endTag?"/":"",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name),m_level);
1349 }
1350 }
1351 break;
1352 default:
1353 char tmp[20];
1354 qsnprintf(tmp,20,"<h%d>tag",m_level);
1355 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant(),tok,children(),tmp);
1356 }
1357 }
1358 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1359 }
1360 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1361 {
1362 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected end of comment while inside"
1363 " <h%d> tag",m_level);
1364 }
1365endheader:
1366 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant(),children());
1367 return retval;
1368}
1369//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1370
1371void DocHtmlSummary::parse()
1372{
1373 AUTO_TRACE();
1374 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1375 parser()->tokenizer.setStateTitle();
1376 Token tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1377 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1378 {
1379 HtmlTagType tagId = HtmlTagType::UNKNOWN;
1380 // check of </summary>
1381 if (tok.value()==TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG &&
1382 (tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name))==HtmlTagType::XML_SUMMARY &&
1383 parser()->context.token->endTag
1384 )
1385 {
1386 break;
1387 }
1388 else if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children()))
1389 {
1390 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant(),tok,children(),"summary section");
1391 }
1392 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1393 }
1394 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
1395 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1396 {
1397 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected end of comment while inside"
1398 " <summary> tag");
1399 }
1400}
1401
1402//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1403
1404Token DocHtmlDetails::parse()
1405{
1406 AUTO_TRACE();
1407 Token retval(TokenRetval::TK_NONE);
1408 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1409
1410 // parse one or more paragraphs
1411 bool isFirst=TRUE;
1412 DocPara *par=nullptr;
1413 do
1414 {
1415 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
1416 par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
1417 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
1418 retval=par->parse();
1419 }
1420 while (retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA));
1421 if (par) par->markLast();
1422
1423 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1424 {
1425 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while inside <details> block");
1426 }
1427
1428 if (!summary())
1429 {
1430 HtmlAttribList summaryAttribs;
1431 m_summary = createDocNode<DocHtmlSummary>(parser(),thisVariant(),summaryAttribs);
1432 DocHtmlSummary *summary = &std::get<DocHtmlSummary>(*m_summary);
1433 summary->children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant(),theTranslator->trDetails());
1434 }
1435 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
1436 return retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_EndHtmlDetails) ? Token::make_RetVal_OK() : retval;
1437}
1438
1439void DocHtmlDetails::parseSummary(DocNodeVariant *parent,HtmlAttribList &attribs)
1440{
1441 AUTO_TRACE();
1442 m_summary = createDocNode<DocHtmlSummary>(parser(),parent,attribs);
1443 DocHtmlSummary *summary = &std::get<DocHtmlSummary>(*m_summary);
1444 summary->parse();
1445}
1446
1447//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1448
1449Token DocHRef::parse()
1450{
1451 AUTO_TRACE();
1452 Token retval(TokenRetval::RetVal_OK);
1453 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1454
1455 Token tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1456 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1457 {
1458 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children()))
1459 {
1460 switch (tok.value())
1461 {
1462 case TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG:
1463 {
1464 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1465 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_A && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </a> tag
1466 {
1467 goto endhref;
1468 }
1469 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_BR)
1470 {
1471 children().append<DocLineBreak>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->attribs);
1472 }
1473 else
1474 {
1475 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected html tag <%s%s> found within <a href=...> context",
1476 parser()->context.token->endTag?"/":"",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
1477 }
1478 }
1479 break;
1480 default:
1481 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant(),tok,children(),"<a>..</a> block");
1482 break;
1483 }
1484 }
1485 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1486 }
1487 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1488 {
1489 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected end of comment while inside"
1490 " <a href=...> tag");
1491 }
1492endhref:
1493 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant(),children());
1494 return retval;
1495}
1496
1497//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1498
1499Token DocInternal::parse(int level)
1500{
1501 AUTO_TRACE();
1502 Token retval(TokenRetval::RetVal_OK);
1503 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1504
1505 // first parse any number of paragraphs
1506 bool isFirst=TRUE;
1507 DocPara *lastPar=nullptr;
1508 do
1509 {
1510 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
1511 DocPara *par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
1512 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
1513 retval=par->parse();
1514 if (!par->isEmpty())
1515 {
1516 if (lastPar) lastPar->markLast(FALSE);
1517 lastPar=par;
1518 }
1519 else
1520 {
1521 children().pop_back();
1522 }
1523 if (retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_LISTITEM))
1524 {
1525 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Invalid list item found");
1526 }
1527 } while (!retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF,
1528 TokenRetval::RetVal_Section, TokenRetval::RetVal_Subsection, TokenRetval::RetVal_Subsubsection,
1529 TokenRetval::RetVal_Paragraph, TokenRetval::RetVal_SubParagraph, TokenRetval::RetVal_SubSubParagraph,
1530 TokenRetval::RetVal_EndInternal));
1531 if (lastPar) lastPar->markLast();
1532
1533 // then parse any number of level-n sections
1534 while ((level==1 && retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_Section)) ||
1535 (level==2 && retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_Subsection)) ||
1536 (level==3 && retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_Subsubsection)) ||
1537 (level==4 && retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_Paragraph)) ||
1538 (level==5 && retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_SubParagraph)) ||
1539 (level==6 && retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_SubSubParagraph))
1540 )
1541 {
1542 children().append<DocSection>(parser(),thisVariant(),
1543 level,
1544 parser()->context.token->sectionId);
1545 retval = children().get_last<DocSection>()->parse();
1546 }
1547
1548 if (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_Internal))
1549 {
1550 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"\\internal command found inside internal section");
1551 }
1552
1553 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
1554 return retval;
1555}
1556
1557//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1558
1559Token DocIndexEntry::parse()
1560{
1561 AUTO_TRACE();
1562 Token retval(TokenRetval::RetVal_OK);
1563 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1564 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1565 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
1566 {
1567 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\addindex command");
1568 goto endindexentry;
1569 }
1570 parser()->tokenizer.setStateTitle();
1571 m_entry="";
1572 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1573 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1574 {
1575 switch (tok.value())
1576 {
1577 case TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE:
1578 m_entry+=" ";
1579 break;
1580 case TokenRetval::TK_WORD:
1581 case TokenRetval::TK_LNKWORD:
1582 m_entry+=parser()->context.token->name;
1583 break;
1584 case TokenRetval::TK_SYMBOL:
1585 {
1586 HtmlEntityMapper::SymType s = DocSymbol::decodeSymbol(parser()->context.token->name);
1587 switch (s)
1588 {
1589 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_BSlash: m_entry+='\\'; break;
1590 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_At: m_entry+='@'; break;
1591 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Less: m_entry+='<'; break;
1592 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Greater: m_entry+='>'; break;
1593 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Amp: m_entry+='&'; break;
1594 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Dollar: m_entry+='$'; break;
1595 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Hash: m_entry+='#'; break;
1596 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Percent: m_entry+='%'; break;
1597 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_apos: m_entry+='\''; break;
1598 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Quot: m_entry+='"'; break;
1599 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_lsquo: m_entry+='`'; break;
1600 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_rsquo: m_entry+='\''; break;
1601 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_ldquo: m_entry+="``"; break;
1602 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_rdquo: m_entry+="''"; break;
1603 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_ndash: m_entry+="--"; break;
1604 case HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_mdash: m_entry+="---"; break;
1605 default:
1606 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected symbol '%s' found as argument of \\addindex",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
1607 break;
1608 }
1609 }
1610 break;
1611 case TokenRetval::TK_COMMAND_AT:
1612 // fall through
1613 case TokenRetval::TK_COMMAND_BS:
1614 switch (Mappers::cmdMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name))
1615 {
1616 case CommandType::CMD_BSLASH: m_entry+='\\'; break;
1617 case CommandType::CMD_AT: m_entry+='@'; break;
1618 case CommandType::CMD_LESS: m_entry+='<'; break;
1619 case CommandType::CMD_GREATER: m_entry+='>'; break;
1620 case CommandType::CMD_AMP: m_entry+='&'; break;
1621 case CommandType::CMD_DOLLAR: m_entry+='$'; break;
1622 case CommandType::CMD_HASH: m_entry+='#'; break;
1623 case CommandType::CMD_DCOLON: m_entry+="::"; break;
1624 case CommandType::CMD_PERCENT: m_entry+='%'; break;
1625 case CommandType::CMD_NDASH: m_entry+="--"; break;
1626 case CommandType::CMD_MDASH: m_entry+="---"; break;
1627 case CommandType::CMD_QUOTE: m_entry+='"'; break;
1628 case CommandType::CMD_PUNT: m_entry+='.'; break;
1629 case CommandType::CMD_PLUS: m_entry+='+'; break;
1630 case CommandType::CMD_MINUS: m_entry+='-'; break;
1631 case CommandType::CMD_EQUAL: m_entry+='='; break;
1632 default:
1633 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected command %s found as argument of \\addindex",
1634 qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
1635 break;
1636 }
1637 break;
1638 default:
1639 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected token %s",
1640 tok.to_string());
1641 break;
1642 }
1643 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1644 }
1645 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
1646 m_entry = m_entry.stripWhiteSpace();
1647endindexentry:
1648 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
1649 return retval;
1650}

1652//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1653
1654DocHtmlCaption::DocHtmlCaption(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,const HtmlAttribList &attribs)
1655 : DocCompoundNode(parser,parent)
1656{
1657 m_hasCaptionId = FALSE;
1658 for (const auto &opt : attribs)
1659 {
1660 if (opt.name=="id" && !opt.value.isEmpty()) // interpret id attribute as an anchor
1661 {
1662 const SectionInfo *sec = SectionManager::instance().find(opt.value);
1663 if (sec)
1664 {
1665 //printf("Found anchor %s\n",qPrint(id));
1666 m_file = sec->fileName();
1667 m_anchor = sec->label();
1668 m_hasCaptionId = TRUE;
1669 }
1670 else
1671 {
1672 warn_doc_error(parser->context.fileName,parser->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Invalid caption id '%s'",qPrint(opt.value));
1673 }
1674 }
1675 else // copy attribute
1676 {
1677 m_attribs.push_back(opt);
1678 }
1679 }
1680}
1681
1682Token DocHtmlCaption::parse()
1683{
1684 AUTO_TRACE();
1685 Token retval = Token::make_TK_NONE();
1686 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1687 Token tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1688 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1689 {
1690 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children()))
1691 {
1692 switch (tok.value())
1693 {
1694 case TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG:
1695 {
1696 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1697 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_CAPTION && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </caption> tag
1698 {
1699 retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
1700 goto endcaption;
1701 }
1702 else
1703 {
1704 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected html tag <%s%s> found within <caption> context",
1705 parser()->context.token->endTag?"/":"",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
1706 }
1707 }
1708 break;
1709 default:
1710 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant(),tok,children(),"<caption> tag");
1711 break;
1712 }
1713 }
1714 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1715 }
1716 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
1717 {
1718 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected end of comment while inside"
1719 " <caption> tag");
1720 }
1721endcaption:
1722 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant(),children());
1723 return retval;
1724}

1726//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1727
1728Token DocHtmlCell::parse()
1729{
1730 AUTO_TRACE();
1731 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
1732 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1733
1734 // parse one or more paragraphs
1735 bool isFirst=TRUE;
1736 DocPara *par=nullptr;
1737 do
1738 {
1739 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
1740 par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
1741 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
1742 retval=par->parse();
1743 if (retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG))
1744 {
1745 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1746 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_TD && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </td> tag
1747 {
1748 retval = Token::make_TK_NEWPARA(); // ignore the tag
1749 }
1750 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_TH && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </th> tag
1751 {
1752 retval = Token::make_TK_NEWPARA(); // ignore the tag
1753 }
1754 }
1755 }
1756 while (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA,TokenRetval::RetVal_EndParBlock));
1757 if (par) par->markLast();
1758
1759 return retval;
1760}
1761
1762Token DocHtmlCell::parseXml()
1763{
1764 AUTO_TRACE();
1765 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
1766 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1767
1768 // parse one or more paragraphs
1769 bool isFirst=TRUE;
1770 DocPara *par=nullptr;
1771 do
1772 {
1773 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
1774 par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
1775 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
1776 retval=par->parse();
1777 if (retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG))
1778 {
1779 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1780 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::XML_ITEM && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </item> tag
1781 {
1782 retval = Token::make_TK_NEWPARA(); // ignore the tag
1783 }
1784 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::XML_DESCRIPTION && parser()->context.token->endTag) // found </description> tag
1785 {
1786 retval = Token::make_TK_NEWPARA(); // ignore the tag
1787 }
1788 }
1789 }
1790 while (retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA));
1791 if (par) par->markLast();
1792
1793 return retval;
1794}
1795
1796uint32_t DocHtmlCell::rowSpan() const
1797{
1798 for (const auto &attr : attribs())
1799 {
1800 if (attr.name.lower()=="rowspan")
1801 {
1802 return attr.value.toUInt();
1803 }
1804 }
1805 return 0;
1806}
1807
1808uint32_t DocHtmlCell::colSpan() const
1809{
1810 for (const auto &attr : attribs())
1811 {
1812 if (attr.name.lower()=="colspan")
1813 {
1814 return std::max(1u,attr.value.toUInt());
1815 }
1816 }
1817 return 1;
1818}
1819
1820DocHtmlCell::Alignment DocHtmlCell::alignment() const
1821{
1822 for (const auto &attr : attribs())
1823 {
1824 QCString attrName = attr.name.lower();
1825 QCString attrValue = attr.value.lower();
1826 if (attrName=="align")
1827 {
1828 if (attrValue=="center")
1829 return Center;
1830 else if (attrValue=="right")
1831 return Right;
1832 else return Left;
1833 }
1834 else if (attrName=="class" && attrValue.startsWith("markdowntable"))
1835 {
1836 if (attrValue=="markdowntableheadcenter")
1837 return Center;
1838 else if (attrValue=="markdowntableheadright")
1839 return Right;
1840 else if (attrValue=="markdowntableheadleft")
1841 return Left;
1842 else if (attrValue=="markdowntableheadnone")
1843 return Center;
1844 else if (attrValue=="markdowntablebodycenter")
1845 return Center;
1846 else if (attrValue=="markdowntablebodyright")
1847 return Right;
1848 else if (attrValue=="markdowntablebodyleft")
1849 return Left;
1850 else if (attrValue=="markdowntablebodynone")
1851 return Left;
1852 else return Left;
1853 }
1854 }
1855 return Left;
1856}
1857
1858DocHtmlCell::Valignment DocHtmlCell::valignment() const
1859{
1860 for (const auto &attr : attribs())
1861 {
1862 QCString attrName = attr.name.lower();
1863 QCString attrValue = attr.value.lower();
1864 if (attrName=="valign")
1865 {
1866 if (attrValue=="top")
1867 return Top;
1868 else if (attrValue=="bottom")
1869 return Bottom;
1870 else if (attrValue=="middle")
1871 return Middle;
1872 else return Middle;
1873 }
1874 }
1875 return Middle;
1876}
1877
1878//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1879
1880bool DocHtmlRow::isHeading() const
1881{ // a row is a table heading if all cells are marked as such
1882 bool heading=TRUE;
1883 for (const auto &n : children())
1884 {
1885 const DocHtmlCell *cell = std::get_if<DocHtmlCell>(&n);
1886 if (cell && !cell->isHeading())
1887 {
1888 heading = FALSE;
1889 break;
1890 }
1891 }
1892 return !children().empty() && heading;
1893}
1894
1895Token DocHtmlRow::parse()
1896{
1897 AUTO_TRACE();
1898 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
1899 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1900
1901 bool isHeading=FALSE;
1902 bool isFirst=TRUE;
1903 DocHtmlCell *cell=nullptr;
1904
1905 // get next token
1906 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1907 // skip whitespace
1908 while (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE,TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA)) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1909 // should find a html tag now
1910 if (tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG))
1911 {
1912 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1913 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_TD && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <td> tag
1914 {
1915 }
1916 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_TH && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <th> tag
1917 {
1918 isHeading=TRUE;
1919 }
1920 else // found some other tag
1921 {
1922 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <td> or <th> tag but "
1923 "found <%s> instead!",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
1924 parser()->tokenizer.pushBackHtmlTag(parser()->context.token->name);
1925 goto endrow;
1926 }
1927 }
1928 else if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) // premature end of comment
1929 {
1930 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while looking"
1931 " for a html description title");
1932 goto endrow;
1933 }
1934 else // token other than html token
1935 {
1936 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <td> or <th> tag but found %s token instead!",
1937 tok.to_string());
1938 goto endrow;
1939 }
1940
1941 // parse one or more cells
1942 do
1943 {
1944 children().append<DocHtmlCell>(parser(),thisVariant(),
1945 parser()->context.token->attribs,
1946 isHeading);
1947 cell = children().get_last<DocHtmlCell>();
1948 cell->markFirst(isFirst);
1949 isFirst=FALSE;
1950 retval=cell->parse();
1951 isHeading = retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_TableHCell);
1952 }
1953 while (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::RetVal_TableCell,TokenRetval::RetVal_TableHCell));
1954 cell->markLast(TRUE);
1955
1956endrow:
1957 return retval;
1958}
1959
1960Token DocHtmlRow::parseXml(bool isHeading)
1961{
1962 AUTO_TRACE();
1963 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
1964 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
1965
1966 bool isFirst=TRUE;
1967 DocHtmlCell *cell=nullptr;
1968
1969 // get next token
1970 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1971 // skip whitespace
1972 while (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE,TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA)) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
1973 // should find a html tag now
1974 if (tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG))
1975 {
1976 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
1977 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::XML_TERM && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <term> tag
1978 {
1979 }
1980 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::XML_DESCRIPTION && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <description> tag
1981 {
1982 }
1983 else // found some other tag
1984 {
1985 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <term> or <description> tag but "
1986 "found <%s> instead!",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
1987 parser()->tokenizer.pushBackHtmlTag(parser()->context.token->name);
1988 goto endrow;
1989 }
1990 }
1991 else if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) // premature end of comment
1992 {
1993 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while looking"
1994 " for a html description title");
1995 goto endrow;
1996 }
1997 else // token other than html token
1998 {
1999 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <td> or <th> tag but found %s token instead!",
2000 tok.to_string());
2001 goto endrow;
2002 }
2003
2004 do
2005 {
2006 children().append<DocHtmlCell>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->attribs,isHeading);
2007 cell = children().get_last<DocHtmlCell>();
2008 cell->markFirst(isFirst);
2009 isFirst=FALSE;
2010 retval=cell->parseXml();
2011 }
2012 while (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::RetVal_TableCell,TokenRetval::RetVal_TableHCell));
2013 cell->markLast(TRUE);
2014
2015endrow:
2016 return retval;
2017}

2019//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2020
2021bool DocHtmlTable::hasCaption() const
2022{
2023 return m_caption!=nullptr;
2024}
2025
2026const DocNodeVariant *DocHtmlTable::caption() const
2027{
2028 return m_caption.get();
2029}
2030
2031const DocNodeVariant *DocHtmlTable::firstRow() const
2032{
2033 if (!children().empty() && std::holds_alternative<DocHtmlRow>(children().front()))
2034 {
2035 return &children().front();
2036 }
2037 return nullptr;
2038}
2039
2040Token DocHtmlTable::parse()
2041{
2042 AUTO_TRACE();
2043 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
2044 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2045
2046getrow:
2047 // get next token
2048 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2049 // skip whitespace
2050 while (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE,TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA)) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2051 // should find a html tag now
2052 if (tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG))
2053 {
2054 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
2055 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_THEAD && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <thead> tag
2056 {
2057 goto getrow;
2058 }
2059 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_TBODY && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <tbody> tag
2060 {
2061 goto getrow;
2062 }
2063 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_TFOOT && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <tfoot> tag
2064 {
2065 goto getrow;
2066 }
2067 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_TR && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <tr> tag
2068 {
2069 // no caption, just rows
2070 retval = Token::make_RetVal_TableRow();
2071 }
2072 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_CAPTION && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <caption> tag
2073 {
2074 if (m_caption)
2075 {
2076 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"table already has a caption, found another one");
2077 }
2078 else
2079 {
2080 m_caption = createDocNode<DocHtmlCaption>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->attribs);
2081 retval=std::get<DocHtmlCaption>(*m_caption).parse();
2082
2083 if (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_OK)) // caption was parsed ok
2084 {
2085 goto getrow;
2086 }
2087 }
2088 }
2089 else // found wrong token
2090 {
2091 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <tr> or <caption> tag but "
2092 "found <%s%s> instead!", parser()->context.token->endTag ? "/" : "", qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
2093 }
2094 }
2095 else if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) // premature end of comment
2096 {
2097 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while looking"
2098 " for a <tr> or <caption> tag");
2099 }
2100 else // token other than html token
2101 {
2102 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <tr> tag but found %s token instead!",
2103 tok.to_string());
2104 }
2105
2106 // parse one or more rows
2107 while (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_TableRow))
2108 {
2109 children().append<DocHtmlRow>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->attribs);
2110 retval = children().get_last<DocHtmlRow>()->parse();
2111 }
2112
2113 computeTableGrid();
2114
2115 return retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_EndTable) ? Token::make_RetVal_OK() : retval;
2116}
2117
2118Token DocHtmlTable::parseXml()
2119{
2120 AUTO_TRACE();
2121 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
2122 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2123
2124 // get next token
2125 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2126 // skip whitespace
2127 while (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE,TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA)) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2128 // should find a html tag now
2129 HtmlTagType tagId=HtmlTagType::UNKNOWN;
2130 bool isHeader=FALSE;
2131 if (tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG))
2132 {
2133 tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
2134 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::XML_ITEM && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <item> tag
2135 {
2136 retval = Token::make_RetVal_TableRow();
2137 }
2138 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::XML_LISTHEADER && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <listheader> tag
2139 {
2140 retval = Token::make_RetVal_TableRow();
2141 isHeader=TRUE;
2142 }
2143 }
2144
2145 // parse one or more rows
2146 while (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_TableRow))
2147 {
2148 children().append<DocHtmlRow>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->attribs);
2149 DocHtmlRow *tr = children().get_last<DocHtmlRow>();
2150 retval=tr->parseXml(isHeader);
2151 isHeader=FALSE;
2152 }
2153
2154 computeTableGrid();
2155
2156 tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
2157 return tagId==HtmlTagType::XML_LIST && parser()->context.token->endTag ? Token::make_RetVal_OK() : retval;
2158}
2159
2160/** Helper class to compute the grid for an HTML style table */
2161struct ActiveRowSpan
2162{
2163 ActiveRowSpan(uint32_t rows,uint32_t col) : rowsLeft(rows), column(col) {}
2164 uint32_t rowsLeft;
2165 uint32_t column;
2166};
2167
2168/** List of ActiveRowSpan classes. */
2169typedef std::vector<ActiveRowSpan> RowSpanList;
2170
2171/** determines the location of all cells in a grid, resolving row and
2172 column spans. For each the total number of visible cells is computed,
2173 and the total number of visible columns over all rows is stored.
2174 */
2175void DocHtmlTable::computeTableGrid()
2176{
2177 //printf("computeTableGrid()\n");
2178 RowSpanList rowSpans;
2179 uint32_t maxCols=0;
2180 uint32_t rowIdx=1;
2181 for (auto &rowNode : children())
2182 {
2183 uint32_t colIdx=1;
2184 uint32_t cells=0;
2185 DocHtmlRow *row = std::get_if<DocHtmlRow>(&rowNode);
2186 if (row)
2187 {
2188 for (auto &cellNode : row->children())
2189 {
2190 DocHtmlCell *cell = std::get_if<DocHtmlCell>(&cellNode);
2191 if (cell)
2192 {
2193 uint32_t rs = cell->rowSpan();
2194 uint32_t cs = cell->colSpan();
2195
2196 for (size_t i=0;i<rowSpans.size();i++)
2197 {
2198 if (rowSpans[i].rowsLeft>0 &&
2199 rowSpans[i].column==colIdx)
2200 {
2201 colIdx=rowSpans[i].column+1;
2202 cells++;
2203 }
2204 }
2205 if (rs>0) rowSpans.emplace_back(rs,colIdx);
2206 //printf("found cell at (%d,%d)\n",rowIdx,colIdx);
2207 cell->setRowIndex(rowIdx);
2208 cell->setColumnIndex(colIdx);
2209 colIdx+=cs;
2210 cells++;
2211 }
2212 }
2213 for (size_t i=0;i<rowSpans.size();i++)
2214 {
2215 if (rowSpans[i].rowsLeft>0) rowSpans[i].rowsLeft--;
2216 }
2217 row->setVisibleCells(cells);
2218 row->setRowIndex(rowIdx);
2219 rowIdx++;
2220 }
2221 if (colIdx-1>maxCols) maxCols=colIdx-1;
2222 }
2223 m_numCols = maxCols;
2224}
2225
2226//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2227
2228Token DocHtmlDescTitle::parse()
2229{
2230 AUTO_TRACE();
2231 Token retval = Token::make_TK_NONE();
2232 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2233
2234 Token tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2235 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
2236 {
2237 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children()))
2238 {
2239 switch (tok.value())
2240 {
2241 case TokenRetval::TK_COMMAND_AT:
2242 // fall through
2243 case TokenRetval::TK_COMMAND_BS:
2244 {
2245 QCString cmdName=parser()->context.token->name;
2246 bool isJavaLink=FALSE;
2247 switch (Mappers::cmdMapper->map(cmdName))
2248 {
2249 case CommandType::CMD_REF:
2250 {
2251 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2252 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
2253 {
2254 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after '%c%s' command",
2255 tok.command_to_char(),qPrint(cmdName));
2256 }
2257 else
2258 {
2259 parser()->tokenizer.setStateRef();
2260 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex(); // get the reference id
2261 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD))
2262 {
2263 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of '%c%s' command",
2264 tok.to_string(),tok.command_to_char(),qPrint(cmdName));
2265 }
2266 else
2267 {
2268 children().append<DocRef>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->name,parser()->context.context);
2269 children().get_last<DocRef>()->parse();
2270 }
2271 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
2272 }
2273 }
2274 break;
2275 case CommandType::CMD_JAVALINK:
2276 isJavaLink=TRUE;
2277 // fall through
2278 case CommandType::CMD_LINK:
2279 {
2280 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2281 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
2282 {
2283 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
2284 qPrint(cmdName));
2285 }
2286 else
2287 {
2288 parser()->tokenizer.setStateLink();
2289 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2290 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD))
2291 {
2292 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of \\%s command",
2293 tok.to_string(),qPrint(cmdName));
2294 }
2295 else
2296 {
2297 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
2298 children().append<DocLink>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->name);
2299 DocLink *lnk = children().get_last<DocLink>();
2300 QCString leftOver = lnk->parse(isJavaLink);
2301 if (!leftOver.isEmpty())
2302 {
2303 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant(),leftOver);
2304 }
2305 }
2306 }
2307 }
2308
2309 break;
2310 default:
2311 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Illegal command '%c%s' found as part of a <dt> tag",
2312 tok.command_to_char(),qPrint(cmdName));
2313 }
2314 }
2315 break;
2316 case TokenRetval::TK_SYMBOL:
2317 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unsupported symbol '%s' found as part of a <dt> tag",
2318 qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
2319 break;
2320 case TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG:
2321 {
2322 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
2323 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_DD && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <dd> tag
2324 {
2325 retval = Token::make_RetVal_DescData();
2326 goto endtitle;
2327 }
2328 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_DT && parser()->context.token->endTag)
2329 {
2330 // ignore </dt> tag.
2331 }
2332 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_DT)
2333 {
2334 // missing <dt> tag.
2335 retval = Token::make_RetVal_DescTitle();
2336 goto endtitle;
2337 }
2338 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_DL && parser()->context.token->endTag)
2339 {
2340 retval = Token::make_RetVal_EndDesc();
2341 goto endtitle;
2342 }
2343 else if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_A)
2344 {
2345 if (!parser()->context.token->endTag)
2346 {
2347 parser()->handleAHref(thisVariant(),children(),parser()->context.token->attribs);
2348 }
2349 }
2350 else
2351 {
2352 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected html tag <%s%s> found within <dt> context",
2353 parser()->context.token->endTag?"/":"",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
2354 }
2355 }
2356 break;
2357 default:
2358 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected token %s found as part of a <dt> tag",
2359 tok.to_string());
2360 break;
2361 }
2362 }
2363 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2364 }
2365 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
2366 {
2367 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Unexpected end of comment while inside"
2368 " <dt> tag");
2369 }
2370endtitle:
2371 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant(),children());
2372 return retval;
2373}
2374
2375//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2376
2377Token DocHtmlDescData::parse()
2378{
2379 AUTO_TRACE();
2380 m_attribs = parser()->context.token->attribs;
2381 Token retval = Token::make_TK_NONE();
2382 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2383
2384 bool isFirst=TRUE;
2385 DocPara *par=nullptr;
2386 do
2387 {
2388 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
2389 par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
2390 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
2391 retval=par->parse();
2392 }
2393 while (retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA));
2394 if (par) par->markLast();
2395
2396 return retval;
2397}

2399//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2400
2401Token DocHtmlDescList::parse()
2402{
2403 AUTO_TRACE();
2404 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
2405 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2406
2407 // get next token
2408 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2409 // skip whitespace
2410 while (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE,TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA)) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2411 // should find a html tag now
2412 if (tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG))
2413 {
2414 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
2415 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_DT && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <dt> tag
2416 {
2417 // continue
2418 }
2419 else // found some other tag
2420 {
2421 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <dt> tag but "
2422 "found <%s> instead!",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
2423 parser()->tokenizer.pushBackHtmlTag(parser()->context.token->name);
2424 goto enddesclist;
2425 }
2426 }
2427 else if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) // premature end of comment
2428 {
2429 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while looking"
2430 " for a html description title");
2431 goto enddesclist;
2432 }
2433 else // token other than html token
2434 {
2435 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <dt> tag but found %s token instead!",
2436 tok.to_string());
2437 goto enddesclist;
2438 }
2439
2440 do
2441 {
2442 children().append<DocHtmlDescTitle>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->attribs);
2443 DocHtmlDescTitle *dt = children().get_last<DocHtmlDescTitle>();
2444 children().append<DocHtmlDescData>(parser(),thisVariant());
2445 DocHtmlDescData *dd = children().get_last<DocHtmlDescData>();
2446 retval=dt->parse();
2447 if (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_DescData))
2448 {
2449 retval=dd->parse();
2450 while (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_DescData))
2451 {
2452 children().append<DocHtmlDescData>(parser(),thisVariant());
2453 dd = children().get_last<DocHtmlDescData>();
2454 retval=dd->parse();
2455 }
2456 }
2457 else if (!retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_DescTitle))
2458 {
2459 // error
2460 break;
2461 }
2462 } while (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_DescTitle));
2463
2464 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
2465 {
2466 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while inside <dl> block");
2467 }
2468
2469enddesclist:
2470
2471 return retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_EndDesc) ? Token::make_RetVal_OK() : retval;
2472}

2475
2476Token DocHtmlListItem::parse()
2477{
2478 AUTO_TRACE();
2479 Token retval = Token::make_TK_NONE();
2480 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2481
2482 // parse one or more paragraphs
2483 bool isFirst=TRUE;
2484 DocPara *par=nullptr;
2485 do
2486 {
2487 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
2488 par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
2489 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
2490 retval=par->parse();
2491 }
2492 while (retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA));
2493 if (par) par->markLast();
2494
2495 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
2496 return retval;

2499Token DocHtmlListItem::parseXml()
2500{
2501 AUTO_TRACE();
2502 Token retval = Token::make_TK_NONE();
2503 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2504
2505 // parse one or more paragraphs
2506 bool isFirst=TRUE;
2507 DocPara *par=nullptr;
2508 do
2509 {
2510 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
2511 par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
2512 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
2513 retval=par->parse();
2514 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) break;
2515
2516 //printf("new item: retval=%x parser()->context.token->name=%s parser()->context.token->endTag=%d\n",
2517 // retval,qPrint(parser()->context.token->name),parser()->context.token->endTag);
2518 if (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_ListItem))
2519 {
2520 break;
2521 }
2522 }
2523 while (!retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_CloseXml));
2524
2525 if (par) par->markLast();
2526
2527 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
2528 return retval;
2529}
