2531//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2532
2533Token DocHtmlList::parse()
2534{
2535 AUTO_TRACE();
2536 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
2537 int num=1;
2538 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2539
2540 // get next token
2541 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2542 // skip whitespace and paragraph breaks
2543 while (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE,TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA)) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2544 // should find a html tag now
2545 if (tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG))
2546 {
2547 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
2548 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_LI && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <li> tag
2549 {
2550 // ok, we can go on.
2551 }
2552 else if (((m_type==Unordered && tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_UL) ||
2553 (m_type==Ordered && tagId==HtmlTagType::HTML_OL)
2554 ) && parser()->context.token->endTag
2555 ) // found empty list
2556 {
2557 // add dummy item to obtain valid HTML
2558 children().append<DocHtmlListItem>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlAttribList(),1);
2559 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"empty list!");
2560 retval = Token::make_RetVal_EndList();
2561 goto endlist;
2562 }
2563 else // found some other tag
2564 {
2565 // add dummy item to obtain valid HTML
2566 children().append<DocHtmlListItem>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlAttribList(),1);
2567 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <li> tag but "
2568 "found <%s%s> instead!",parser()->context.token->endTag?"/":"",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
2569 parser()->tokenizer.pushBackHtmlTag(parser()->context.token->name);
2570 goto endlist;
2571 }
2572 }
2573 else if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) // premature end of comment
2574 {
2575 // add dummy item to obtain valid HTML
2576 children().append<DocHtmlListItem>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlAttribList(),1);
2577 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while looking"
2578 " for a html list item");
2579 goto endlist;
2580 }
2581 else // token other than html token
2582 {
2583 // add dummy item to obtain valid HTML
2584 children().append<DocHtmlListItem>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlAttribList(),1);
2585 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <li> tag but found %s token instead!",
2586 tok.to_string());
2587 goto endlist;
2588 }
2589
2590 do
2591 {
2592 children().append<DocHtmlListItem>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->attribs,num++);
2593 DocHtmlListItem *li = children().get_last<DocHtmlListItem>();
2594 retval=li->parse();
2595 } while (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_ListItem));
2596
2597 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
2598 {
2599 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while inside <%cl> block",
2600 m_type==Unordered ? 'u' : 'o');
2601 }
2602
2603endlist:
2604 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
2605 return retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_EndList) ? Token::make_RetVal_OK() : retval;
2606}
2607
2608Token DocHtmlList::parseXml()
2609{
2610 AUTO_TRACE();
2611 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
2612 int num=1;
2613 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2614
2615 // get next token
2616 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2617 // skip whitespace and paragraph breaks
2618 while (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE,TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA)) tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2619 // should find a html tag now
2620 if (tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_HTMLTAG))
2621 {
2622 HtmlTagType tagId=Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name);
2623 //printf("parser()->context.token->name=%s parser()->context.token->endTag=%d\n",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name),parser()->context.token->endTag);
2624 if (tagId==HtmlTagType::XML_ITEM && !parser()->context.token->endTag) // found <item> tag
2625 {
2626 // ok, we can go on.
2627 }
2628 else // found some other tag
2629 {
2630 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <item> tag but "
2631 "found <%s> instead!",qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
2632 parser()->tokenizer.pushBackHtmlTag(parser()->context.token->name);
2633 goto endlist;
2634 }
2635 }
2636 else if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) // premature end of comment
2637 {
2638 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while looking"
2639 " for a html list item");
2640 goto endlist;
2641 }
2642 else // token other than html token
2643 {
2644 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected <item> tag but found %s token instead!",
2645 tok.to_string());
2646 goto endlist;
2647 }
2648
2649 do
2650 {
2651 children().append<DocHtmlListItem>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->attribs,num++);
2652 DocHtmlListItem *li = children().get_last<DocHtmlListItem>();
2653 retval=li->parseXml();
2654 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) break;
2655 //printf("retval=%x parser()->context.token->name=%s\n",retval,qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
2656 } while (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_ListItem));
2657
2658 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
2659 {
2660 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while inside <list type=\"%s\"> block",
2661 m_type==Unordered ? "bullet" : "number");
2662 }
2663
2664endlist:
2665 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
2666 return (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::RetVal_EndList,TokenRetval::RetVal_CloseXml) || parser()->context.token->name=="list") ?
2667 Token::make_RetVal_OK() : retval;
2668}
2669
2670//--------------------------------------------------------------------------
2671
2672Token DocHtmlBlockQuote::parse()
2673{
2674 AUTO_TRACE();
2675 Token retval = Token::make_TK_NONE();
2676 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2677
2678 // parse one or more paragraphs
2679 bool isFirst=TRUE;
2680 DocPara *par=nullptr;
2681 do
2682 {
2683 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
2684 par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
2685 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
2686 retval=par->parse();
2687 }
2688 while (retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA));
2689 if (par) par->markLast();
2690
2691 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
2692 {
2693 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment while inside <blockquote> block");
2694 }
2695
2696 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
2697 return retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_EndBlockQuote) ? Token::make_RetVal_OK() : retval;
2698}
2699
2700//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2701
2702Token DocParBlock::parse()
2703{
2704 AUTO_TRACE();
2705 Token retval = Token::make_TK_NONE();
2706 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2707
2708 // parse one or more paragraphs
2709 bool isFirst=TRUE;
2710 DocPara *par=nullptr;
2711 do
2712 {
2713 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
2714 par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
2715 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
2716 retval=par->parse();
2717 }
2718 while (retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA));
2719 if (par) par->markLast();
2720
2721 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
2722 return retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_EndBlockQuote) ? Token::make_RetVal_OK() : retval;
2723}

2759//--------------------------------------------------------------------------
2760
2761DocAutoListItem::DocAutoListItem(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,int indent,int num)
2762 : DocCompoundNode(parser,parent), m_indent(indent), m_itemNum(num)
2763{
2764}
2765
2766Token DocAutoListItem::parse()
2767{
2768 AUTO_TRACE();
2769 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
2770 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2771
2772 // first parse any number of paragraphs
2773 bool isFirst=TRUE;
2774 DocPara *lastPar=nullptr;
2775 do
2776 {
2777 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
2778 DocPara *par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
2779 if (isFirst) { par->markFirst(); isFirst=FALSE; }
2780 retval=par->parse();
2781 if (!par->isEmpty())
2782 {
2783 if (lastPar) lastPar->markLast(FALSE);
2784 lastPar=par;
2785 }
2786 else
2787 {
2788 children().pop_back();
2789 }
2790 // next paragraph should be more indented than the - marker to belong
2791 // to this item
2792 } while (retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA) && parser()->context.token->indent>m_indent);
2793 if (lastPar) lastPar->markLast();
2794
2795 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
2796 return retval;
2797}

2799//--------------------------------------------------------------------------
2800
2801DocAutoList::DocAutoList(DocParser *parser,DocNodeVariant *parent,int indent,bool isEnumList,
2802 int depth, bool isCheckedList):
2803 DocCompoundNode(parser,parent), m_indent(indent), m_isEnumList(isEnumList),
2804 m_isCheckedList(isCheckedList), m_depth(depth)
2805{
2806}
2807
2808Token DocAutoList::parse()
2809{
2810 AUTO_TRACE();
2811 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
2812 int num=1;
2813 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2814 parser()->tokenizer.startAutoList();
2815 // first item or sub list => create new list
2816 do
2817 {
2818 switch (parser()->context.token->id)
2819 {
2820 case -1:
2821 break;
2822 case DocAutoList::Unchecked: // unchecked
2823 case DocAutoList::Checked_x: // checked with x
2824 case DocAutoList::Checked_X: // checked with X
2825 num = parser()->context.token->id;
2826 break;
2827 default: // explicitly numbered list
2828 num=parser()->context.token->id; // override num with real number given
2829 break;
2830 }
2831
2832 children().append<DocAutoListItem>(parser(),thisVariant(),m_indent,num++);
2833 retval = children().get_last<DocAutoListItem>()->parse();
2834 //printf("DocAutoList::parse(): retval=0x%x parser()->context.token->indent=%d m_indent=%d "
2835 // "m_isEnumList=%d parser()->context.token->isEnumList=%d parser()->context.token->name=%s\n",
2836 // retval,parser()->context.token->indent,m_indent,m_isEnumList,parser()->context.token->isEnumList,
2837 // qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
2838 //printf("num=%d parser()->context.token->id=%d\n",num,parser()->context.token->id);
2839 }
2840 while (retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_LISTITEM) && // new list item
2841 m_indent==parser()->context.token->indent && // at same indent level
2842 m_isEnumList==parser()->context.token->isEnumList && // of the same kind
2843 m_isCheckedList==parser()->context.token->isCheckedList && // of the same kind
2844 (parser()->context.token->id==-1 || parser()->context.token->id>=num) // increasing number (or no number or checked list)
2845 );
2846
2847 parser()->tokenizer.endAutoList();
2848 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
2849 return retval;
2850}

2852//--------------------------------------------------------------------------
2853
2854void DocTitle::parse()
2855{
2856 AUTO_TRACE();
2857 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2858 parser()->tokenizer.setStateTitle();
2859 Token tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2860 while (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE, TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
2861 {
2862 if (!parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children()))
2863 {
2864 parser()->errorHandleDefaultToken(thisVariant(),tok,children(),"title section");
2865 }
2866 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
2867 }
2868 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
2869 parser()->handlePendingStyleCommands(thisVariant(),children());
2870}
2871
2872void DocTitle::parseFromString(DocNodeVariant *parent,const QCString &text)
2873{
2874 parser()->context.insideHtmlLink=TRUE;
2875 parser()->pushContext(); // this will create a new parser->context.token
2876 parser()->internalValidatingParseDoc(thisVariant(),children(),text);
2877 parser()->popContext(); // this will restore the old parser->context.token
2878 parser()->context.insideHtmlLink=FALSE;
2879 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
2880 flattenParagraphs(thisVariant(),children());
2881}

2890bool DocSimpleSect::hasTitle() const
2891{

2893}
2894
2895Token DocSimpleSect::parse(bool userTitle,bool needsSeparator)
2896{
2897 AUTO_TRACE();
2898 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2899
2900 // handle case for user defined title
2901 if (userTitle)
2902 {
2903 m_title = createDocNode<DocTitle>(parser(),thisVariant());
2904 std::get_if<DocTitle>(m_title.get())->parse();
2905 }
2906
2907 // add new paragraph as child
2908 if (!children().empty() && std::holds_alternative<DocPara>(children().back()))
2909 {
2910 std::get<DocPara>(children().back()).markLast(FALSE);
2911 }
2912 bool markFirst = children().empty();
2913 if (needsSeparator)
2914 {
2915 children().append<DocSimpleSectSep>(parser(),thisVariant());
2916 }
2917 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
2918 DocPara *par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
2919 if (markFirst)
2920 {
2921 par->markFirst();
2922 }
2923 par->markLast();
2924
2925 // parse the contents of the paragraph
2926 Token retval = par->parse();
2927
2928 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
2929 return retval; // 0==EOF, TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA, TokenRetval::TK_LISTITEM, TokenRetval::TK_ENDLIST, TokenRetval::RetVal_SimpleSec
2930}
2931
2932Token DocSimpleSect::parseRcs()
2933{
2934 AUTO_TRACE();
2935 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2936
2937 m_title = createDocNode<DocTitle>(parser(),thisVariant());
2938 DocTitle *title = &std::get<DocTitle>(*m_title);
2939 title->parseFromString(thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->name);
2940
2941 QCString text = parser()->context.token->text;
2942 parser()->pushContext(); // this will create a new parser->context.token
2943 parser()->internalValidatingParseDoc(thisVariant(),children(),text);
2944 parser()->popContext(); // this will restore the old parser->context.token
2945
2946 return Token::make_RetVal_OK();
2947}
2948
2949Token DocSimpleSect::parseXml()
2950{
2951 AUTO_TRACE();
2952 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
2953
2954 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
2955 for (;;)
2956 {
2957 // add new paragraph as child
2958 if (!children().empty() && std::holds_alternative<DocPara>(children().back()))
2959 {
2960 std::get<DocPara>(children().back()).markLast(false);
2961 }
2962 bool markFirst = children().empty();
2963 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
2964 DocPara *par = children().get_last<DocPara>();
2965 if (markFirst)
2966 {
2967 par->markFirst();
2968 }
2969 par->markLast();
2970
2971 // parse the contents of the paragraph
2972 retval = par->parse();
2973 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) break;
2974 if (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_CloseXml))
2975 {
2976 retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
2977 break;
2978 }
2979 }
2980
2981 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
2982 return retval;
2983}
2984
2985void DocSimpleSect::appendLinkWord(const QCString &word)
2986{
2987 DocPara *p=nullptr;
2988 if (children().empty() || (p=std::get_if<DocPara>(&children().back()))==nullptr)
2989 {
2990 children().append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
2991 p = children().get_last<DocPara>();
2992 }
2993 else
2994 {
2995 // Comma-separate <seealso> links.
2996 p->injectToken(Token::make_TK_WORD(),",");
2997 p->injectToken(Token::make_TK_WHITESPACE()," ");
2998 }
2999
3000 parser()->context.inSeeBlock=TRUE;
3001 p->injectToken(Token::make_TK_LNKWORD(),word);
3002 parser()->context.inSeeBlock=FALSE;
3003}
3004
3005QCString DocSimpleSect::typeString() const
3006{
3007 switch (m_type)
3008 {
3009 case Unknown: break;
3010 case See: return "see";
3011 case Return: return "return";
3012 case Author: // fall through
3013 case Authors: return "author";
3014 case Version: return "version";
3015 case Since: return "since";
3016 case Date: return "date";
3017 case Note: return "note";
3018 case Warning: return "warning";
3019 case Pre: return "pre";
3020 case Post: return "post";
3021 case Copyright: return "copyright";
3022 case Invar: return "invariant";
3023 case Remark: return "remark";
3024 case Attention: return "attention";
3025 case Important: return "important";
3026 case User: return "user";
3027 case Rcs: return "rcs";
3028 }
3029 return "unknown";
3030}
3031
3032//--------------------------------------------------------------------------
3033
3034Token DocParamList::parse(const QCString &cmdName)
3035{
3036 AUTO_TRACE();
3037 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
3038 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
3039 DocPara *par=nullptr;
3040 QCString saveCmdName = cmdName;
3041
3042 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3043 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
3044 {
3045 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
3046 qPrint(saveCmdName));
3047 retval = Token::make_RetVal_EndParBlock();
3048 goto endparamlist;
3049 }
3050 parser()->tokenizer.setStateParam();
3051 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3052 while (tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD)) /* there is a parameter name */
3053 {
3054 if (m_type==DocParamSect::Param)
3055 {
3056 int typeSeparator = parser()->context.token->name.find('#'); // explicit type position
3057 if (typeSeparator!=-1)
3058 {
3059 parser()->handleParameterType(thisVariant(),m_paramTypes,parser()->context.token->name.left(typeSeparator));
3060 parser()->context.token->name = parser()->context.token->name.mid(typeSeparator+1);
3061 parser()->context.hasParamCommand=TRUE;
3062 parser()->checkArgumentName();
3063 if (parent() && std::holds_alternative<DocParamSect>(*parent()))
3064 {
3065 std::get<DocParamSect>(*parent()).m_hasTypeSpecifier=true;
3066 }
3067 }
3068 else
3069 {
3070 parser()->context.hasParamCommand=TRUE;
3071 parser()->checkArgumentName();
3072 }
3073 }
3074 else if (m_type==DocParamSect::RetVal)
3075 {
3076 parser()->context.hasReturnCommand=TRUE;
3077 parser()->checkRetvalName();
3078 }
3079 //m_params.append(parser()->context.token->name);
3080 parser()->handleLinkedWord(thisVariant(),m_params);
3081 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3082 }
3083 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3084 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) // premature end of comment
3085 {
3086 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment block while parsing the "
3087 "argument of command %s",qPrint(saveCmdName));
3088 retval = Token::make_RetVal_EndParBlock();
3089 goto endparamlist;
3090 }
3091 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE)) /* premature end of comment block */
3092 {
3093 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA)) /* empty param description */
3094 {
3095 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s in comment block while parsing the "
3096 "argument of command %s",tok.to_string(),qPrint(saveCmdName));
3097 }
3098 retval = Token::make_RetVal_EndParBlock();
3099 goto endparamlist;
3100 }
3101
3102 m_paragraphs.append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
3103 par = m_paragraphs.get_last<DocPara>();
3104 retval = par->parse();
3105 par->markFirst();
3106 par->markLast();
3107
3108endparamlist:
3109 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
3110 return retval;
3111}
3112
3113Token DocParamList::parseXml(const QCString &paramName)
3114{
3115 AUTO_TRACE();
3116 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
3117 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
3118
3119 parser()->context.token->name = paramName;
3120 if (m_type==DocParamSect::Param)
3121 {
3122 parser()->context.hasParamCommand=TRUE;
3123 parser()->checkArgumentName();
3124 }
3125 else if (m_type==DocParamSect::RetVal)
3126 {
3127 parser()->context.hasReturnCommand=TRUE;
3128 parser()->checkRetvalName();
3129 }
3130
3131 parser()->handleLinkedWord(thisVariant(),m_params);
3132
3133 do
3134 {
3135 m_paragraphs.append<DocPara>(parser(),thisVariant());
3136 DocPara *par = m_paragraphs.get_last<DocPara>();
3137 retval = par->parse();
3138 if (par->isEmpty()) // avoid adding an empty paragraph for the whitespace
3139 // after </para> and before </param>
3140 {
3141 m_paragraphs.pop_back();
3142 break;
3143 }
3144 else // append the paragraph to the list
3145 {
3146 if (!m_paragraphs.empty())
3147 {
3148 m_paragraphs.get_last<DocPara>()->markLast(FALSE);
3149 }
3150 bool markFirst = m_paragraphs.empty();
3151 par = &std::get<DocPara>(m_paragraphs.back());
3152 if (markFirst)
3153 {
3154 par->markFirst();
3155 }
3156 par->markLast();
3157 }
3158
3159 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) break;
3160
3161 } while (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_CloseXml) &&
3162 Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name)!=HtmlTagType::XML_PARAM &&
3163 Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name)!=HtmlTagType::XML_TYPEPARAM &&
3164 Mappers::htmlTagMapper->map(parser()->context.token->name)!=HtmlTagType::XML_EXCEPTION);
3165
3166 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF)) /* premature end of comment block */
3167 {
3168 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unterminated param or exception tag");
3169 }
3170 else
3171 {
3172 retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
3173 }
3174
3175 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
3176 return retval;
3177}

3179//--------------------------------------------------------------------------
3180
3181Token DocParamSect::parse(const QCString &cmdName,bool xmlContext, Direction d)
3182{
3183 AUTO_TRACE();
3184 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
3185 auto ns = AutoNodeStack(parser(),thisVariant());
3186
3187 if (d!=Unspecified)
3188 {
3189 m_hasInOutSpecifier=TRUE;
3190 }
3191
3192 if (!children().empty() && std::holds_alternative<DocParamList>(children().back()))
3193 {
3194 DocParamList &lastPl = std::get<DocParamList>(children().back());
3195 lastPl.markLast(false);
3196 }
3197 bool markFirst = children().empty();
3198 children().append<DocParamList>(parser(),thisVariant(),m_type,d);
3199 DocParamList *pl = children().get_last<DocParamList>();
3200 if (markFirst)
3201 {
3202 pl->markFirst();
3203 }
3204 pl->markLast();
3205 if (xmlContext)
3206 {
3207 retval = pl->parseXml(cmdName);
3208 }
3209 else
3210 {
3211 retval = pl->parse(cmdName);
3212 }
3213 if (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_EndParBlock))
3214 {
3215 retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
3216 }
3217
3218 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
3219 return retval;
3220}

3229
3230Token DocPara::handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Type t, bool xmlContext)
3231{
3232 AUTO_TRACE();
3233 DocSimpleSect *ss=nullptr;
3234 bool needsSeparator = FALSE;
3235 if (!children().empty() && // has previous element
3236 (ss=children().get_last<DocSimpleSect>()) && // was a simple sect
3237 ss->type()==t && // of same type
3238 t!=DocSimpleSect::User) // but not user defined
3239 {
3240 // append to previous section
3241 needsSeparator = TRUE;
3242 }
3243 else // start new section
3244 {
3245 children().append<DocSimpleSect>(parser(),thisVariant(),t);
3246 ss = children().get_last<DocSimpleSect>();
3247 }
3248 Token rv = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
3249 if (xmlContext)
3250 {
3251 return ss->parseXml();
3252 }
3253 else
3254 {
3255 rv = ss->parse(t==DocSimpleSect::User,needsSeparator);
3256 }
3257 return (!rv.is(TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA)) ? rv : Token::make_RetVal_OK();
3258}
3259
3260Token DocPara::handleParamSection(const QCString &cmdName,
3261 DocParamSect::Type t,
3262 bool xmlContext=FALSE,
3263 int direction=DocParamSect::Unspecified)
3264{
3265 AUTO_TRACE();
3266 DocParamSect *ps = nullptr;
3267 if (!children().empty() && // previous element
3268 (ps=children().get_last<DocParamSect>()) && // was a param sect
3269 ps->type()==t) // of same type
3270 { // append to previous section ps
3271 }
3272 else // start new section
3273 {
3274 children().append<DocParamSect>(parser(),thisVariant(),t);
3275 ps = children().get_last<DocParamSect>();
3276 }
3277 Token rv=ps->parse(cmdName,xmlContext,
3278 static_cast<DocParamSect::Direction>(direction));
3279 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",rv.to_string());
3280 return (!rv.is(TokenRetval::TK_NEWPARA)) ? rv : Token::make_RetVal_OK();
3281}
3282
3283void DocPara::handleCite(char cmdChar,const QCString &cmdName)
3284{
3285 AUTO_TRACE();
3286 // get the argument of the cite command.
3287 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3288 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
3289 {
3290 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after '%c%s' command",
3291 cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3292 return;
3293 }
3294 parser()->tokenizer.setStateCite();
3295 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3296 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
3297 {
3298 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment block while parsing the "
3299 "argument of command '%c%s'",cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3300 return;
3301 }
3302 else if (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WORD,TokenRetval::TK_LNKWORD))
3303 {
3304 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of '%c%s'",
3305 tok.to_string(),cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3306 return;
3307 }
3308 parser()->context.token->sectionId = parser()->context.token->name;
3309 children().append<DocCite>(
3310 parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->name,parser()->context.context);
3311
3312 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3313}
3314
3315void DocPara::handleEmoji(char cmdChar,const QCString &cmdName)
3316{
3317 AUTO_TRACE();
3318 // get the argument of the emoji command.
3319 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3320 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
3321 {
3322 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after '%c%s' command",
3323 cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3324 return;
3325 }
3326 parser()->tokenizer.setStateEmoji();
3327 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3328 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
3329 {
3330 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"no emoji name given or unexpected end of comment block while parsing the "
3331 "argument of command '%c%s'",cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3332 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3333 return;
3334 }
3335 else if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD))
3336 {
3337 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of '%c%s'",
3338 tok.to_string(),cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3339 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3340 return;
3341 }
3342 children().append<DocEmoji>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->name);
3343 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3344}
3345
3346void DocPara::handleDoxyConfig(char cmdChar,const QCString &cmdName)
3347{
3348 // get the argument of the cite command.
3349 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3350 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
3351 {
3352 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after '%c%s' command",
3353 cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3354 return;
3355 }
3356 parser()->tokenizer.setStateDoxyConfig();
3357 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3358 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
3359 {
3360 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment block while parsing the "
3361 "argument of command '%c%s'",cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3362 return;
3363 }
3364 else if (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WORD,TokenRetval::TK_LNKWORD))
3365 {
3366 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of '%c%s'",
3367 tok.to_string(),cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3368 return;
3369 }
3370 ConfigOption * opt = ConfigImpl::instance()->get(parser()->context.token->name);
3371 if (opt)
3372 {
3373 QCString optionValue;
3374 switch (opt->kind())
3375 {
3376 case ConfigOption::O_Bool:
3377 optionValue = *(static_cast<ConfigBool*>(opt)->valueStringRef());
3378 break;
3379 case ConfigOption::O_String:
3380 optionValue = *(static_cast<ConfigString*>(opt)->valueRef());
3381 break;
3382 case ConfigOption::O_Enum:
3383 optionValue = *(static_cast<ConfigEnum*>(opt)->valueRef());
3384 break;
3385 case ConfigOption::O_Int:
3386 optionValue = *(static_cast<ConfigInt*>(opt)->valueStringRef());
3387 break;
3388 case ConfigOption::O_List:
3389 {
3390 StringVector *lst = static_cast<ConfigList*>(opt)->valueRef();
3391 optionValue="";
3392 if (!lst->empty())
3393 {
3394 std::string lstFormat = theTranslator->trWriteList(static_cast<int>(lst->size())).str();
3395 static const reg::Ex marker(R"(@(\d+))");
3396 reg::Iterator it(lstFormat,marker);
3397 reg::Iterator end;
3398 size_t index=0;
3399 // now replace all markers with the real text
3400 for ( ; it!=end ; ++it)
3401 {
3402 const auto &match = *it;
3403 size_t newIndex = match.position();
3404 size_t matchLen = match.length();
3405 optionValue += lstFormat.substr(index,newIndex-index);
3406 unsigned long entryIndex = std::stoul(match[1].str());
3407 if (entryIndex<(unsigned long)lst->size())
3408 {
3409 optionValue += lst->at(entryIndex);
3410 }
3411 index=newIndex+matchLen;
3412 }
3413 optionValue+=lstFormat.substr(index);
3414 }
3415 }
3416 break;
3417 case ConfigOption::O_Obsolete:
3418 warn(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(), "Obsolete setting for '%c%s': '%s'",
3419 cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName),qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
3420 break;
3421 case ConfigOption::O_Disabled:
3422 warn(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),
3423 "Disabled setting (i.e. not supported in this doxygen executable) for '%c%s': '%s'",
3424 cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName),qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
3425 break;
3426 case ConfigOption::O_Info:
3427 // nothing to show here
3428 break;
3429 }
3430 if (!optionValue.isEmpty())
3431 {
3432 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant(),optionValue);
3433 }
3434 }
3435 else
3436 {
3437 warn(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(), "Unknown option for '%c%s': '%s'",
3438 cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName),qPrint(parser()->context.token->name));
3439 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->name);
3440 }
3441 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3442}
3443
3444Token DocPara::handleXRefItem()
3445{
3446 AUTO_TRACE();
3447 Token retval=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3448 ASSERT(retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE));
3449 parser()->tokenizer.setStateXRefItem();

3451 if (retval.is(TokenRetval::RetVal_OK))

3460 }

3462 return retval;
3463}
3464
3465void DocPara::handleShowDate(char cmdChar,const QCString &cmdName)
3466{
3467 AUTO_TRACE();
3468 QCString fmt;
3469 QCString date;
3470 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3471 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
3472 {
3473 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after '%c%s' command",
3474 cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3475 return;
3476 }
3477 parser()->tokenizer.setStateQuotedString();
3478 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3479 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD))
3480 {
3481 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"invalid <format> argument for command '%c%s'",
3482 cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3483 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3484 return;
3485 }
3486 fmt = parser()->context.token->name;
3487
3488 parser()->tokenizer.setStateShowDate();
3489 tok = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3490
3491 QCString specDateRaw = tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD) ? parser()->context.token->name : QCString();
3492 QCString specDate = specDateRaw.stripWhiteSpace();
3493 bool specDateOnlyWS = !specDateRaw.isEmpty() && specDate.isEmpty();
3494 if (!specDate.isEmpty() && !tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WORD,TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
3495 {
3496 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"invalid <date_time> argument for command '%c%s'",
3497 cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3498 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3499 return;
3500 }
3501
3502 std::tm dat{};
3503 int specFormat=0;
3504 QCString err = dateTimeFromString(specDate,dat,specFormat);
3505 if (!err.isEmpty())
3506 {
3507 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"invalid <date_time> argument for command '%c%s': %s",
3508 cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName),qPrint(err));
3509 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3510 return;
3511 }
3512
3513 int usedFormat=0;
3514 QCString dateTimeStr = formatDateTime(fmt,dat,usedFormat);
3515
3516 // warn the user if the format contains markers that are not explicitly filled in
3517 for (int i=0;i<SF_NumBits;i++)
3518 {
3519 int bitMask = 1<<i;
3520 if ((usedFormat&bitMask) && !(specFormat&bitMask)) // a part was used in the format string but its value was not specified.
3521 {
3522 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"'%c%s' <format> parameter '%s' has %s related markers which are not specified in the <date_time> parameter '%s'. Filling in the current value for %s instead.",
3523 cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName),
3524 qPrint(fmt),SF_bit2str(i),qPrint(specDate),SF_bit2str(i));
3525 }
3526 }
3527
3528 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant(),dateTimeStr);
3529 if (specDateOnlyWS) // specDate is only whitespace
3530 {
3531 children().append<DocWhiteSpace>(parser(),thisVariant()," ");
3532 }
3533 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3534}

3573
3574void DocPara::handleIncludeOperator(const QCString &cmdName,DocIncOperator::Type t)
3575{
3576 AUTO_TRACE("cmdName={}",cmdName);
3577 QCString saveCmdName = cmdName;
3578 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3579 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
3580 {
3581 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
3582 qPrint(saveCmdName));
3583 return;
3584 }
3585 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePattern();
3586 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3587 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3588 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
3589 {
3590 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment block while parsing the "
3591 "argument of command %s", qPrint(saveCmdName));
3592 return;
3593 }
3594 else if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD))
3595 {
3596 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of %s",
3597 tok.to_string(),qPrint(saveCmdName));
3598 return;
3599 }
3600 auto it1 = children().size()>=1 ? std::prev(children().end()) : children().end();
3601 auto it2 = children().size()>=2 ? std::prev(it1) : children().end();
3602 DocNodeVariant *n1 = it1!=children().end() ? &(*it1) : nullptr;
3603 DocNodeVariant *n2 = it2!=children().end() ? &(*it2) : nullptr;
3604 //TODO get from context the stripCodeComments()
3605 bool stripCodeComments = Config_getBool(STRIP_CODE_COMMENTS);
3606 children().append<DocIncOperator>(parser(),thisVariant(),t,
3607 parser()->context.token->name,
3608 parser()->context.context,
3609 stripCodeComments,
3610 parser()->context.isExample,
3611 parser()->context.exampleName
3612 );
3613 DocIncOperator *op = children().get_last<DocIncOperator>();
3614 DocIncOperator *n1_docIncOp = std::get_if<DocIncOperator>(n1);
3615 DocWhiteSpace *n1_docWs = std::get_if<DocWhiteSpace >(n1);
3616 DocIncOperator *n2_docIncOp = std::get_if<DocIncOperator>(n2);
3617 bool isFirst = !n1 || // no last node
3618 (!n1_docIncOp && !n1_docWs) || // last node is not operator or whitespace
3619 (n1_docWs && n2 && !n2_docIncOp); // last node is not operator
3620 op->markFirst(isFirst);
3621 op->markLast(true);
3622 if (n1_docIncOp)
3623 {
3624 n1_docIncOp->markLast(false);
3625 }
3626 else if (n1_docWs && n2_docIncOp)
3627 {
3628 n2_docIncOp->markLast(false);
3629 }
3630 op->parse();
3631}

3634void DocPara::handleFile(const QCString &cmdName)
3635{
3636 AUTO_TRACE("cmdName={}",cmdName);
3637 QCString saveCmdName = cmdName;
3638 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3639 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
3640 {
3641 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
3642 qPrint(saveCmdName));
3643 return;
3644 }
3645 parser()->tokenizer.setStateFile();
3646 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3647 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();

3649 {
3650 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of %s",
3651 tok.to_string(),qPrint(saveCmdName));

3661 {
3662 children().pop_back();

3673void DocPara::handleLink(const QCString &cmdName,bool isJavaLink)
3674{
3675 AUTO_TRACE("cmdName={} isJavaLink={}",cmdName,isJavaLink);
3676 QCString saveCmdName = cmdName;
3677 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3678 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
3679 {
3680 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
3681 qPrint(saveCmdName));
3682 return;
3683 }
3684 parser()->tokenizer.setStateLink();
3685 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3686 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD))
3687 {
3688 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"%s as the argument of %s",
3689 tok.to_string(),qPrint(saveCmdName));
3690 return;
3691 }
3692 if (saveCmdName == "javalink")
3693 {
3694 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant(),
3695 parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),
3696 DocStyleChange::Code,cmdName,TRUE);
3697 }
3698 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3699 children().append<DocLink>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.token->name);
3700 DocLink *lnk = children().get_last<DocLink>();
3701 if (saveCmdName == "javalink")
3702 {
3703 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant(),
3704 parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),
3705 DocStyleChange::Code,cmdName,FALSE);
3706 }
3707 QCString leftOver = lnk->parse(isJavaLink);
3708 if (!leftOver.isEmpty())
3709 {
3710 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant(),leftOver);
3711 }
3712}

3740
3741void DocPara::handleInclude(const QCString &cmdName,DocInclude::Type t)
3742{
3743 AUTO_TRACE("cmdName={}",cmdName);
3744 QCString saveCmdName = cmdName;
3745 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3746 bool isBlock = false;
3747 bool trimLeft = false;
3748 bool localScope = false;
3749 bool stripCodeComments = Config_getBool(STRIP_CODE_COMMENTS);
3750 if (tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD) && parser()->context.token->name=="{")
3751 {
3752 parser()->tokenizer.setStateOptions();
3753 parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3754 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3755 StringVector optList=split(parser()->context.token->name.str(),",");
3756 auto contains = [&optList](const char *kw)
3757 {
3758 return std::find(optList.begin(),optList.end(),kw)!=optList.end();
3759 };
3760 localScope = contains("local");
3761 if (contains("nostrip"))
3762 {
3763 stripCodeComments = false;
3764 }
3765 else if (contains("strip"))
3766 {
3767 stripCodeComments = true;
3768 }
3769 if (t==DocInclude::Snippet && contains("trimleft"))
3770 {
3771 trimLeft = true;
3772 }
3773
3774 if (contains("lineno"))
3775 {
3776 if (t==DocInclude::Include) t = DocInclude::IncWithLines;
3777 else if (t==DocInclude::Snippet) t = DocInclude::SnippetWithLines;
3778 else if (t==DocInclude::DontInclude) t = DocInclude::DontIncWithLines;
3779 }
3780 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3781 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
3782 {
3783 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
3784 qPrint(saveCmdName));
3785 return;
3786 }
3787 }
3788 else if (tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD) && parser()->context.token->name=="[")
3789 {
3790 parser()->tokenizer.setStateBlock();
3791 parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3792 isBlock = (parser()->context.token->name.stripWhiteSpace() == "block");
3793 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3794 parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3795 }
3796 else if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
3797 {
3798 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after \\%s command",
3799 qPrint(saveCmdName));
3800 return;
3801 }
3802 parser()->tokenizer.setStateFile();
3803 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3804 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3805 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
3806 {
3807 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment block while parsing the "
3808 "argument of command %s",qPrint(saveCmdName));
3809 return;
3810 }
3811 else if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD))
3812 {
3813 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of %s",
3814 tok.to_string(),qPrint(saveCmdName));
3815 return;
3816 }
3817 QCString fileName = parser()->context.token->name;
3818 QCString blockId;
3819 if (t==DocInclude::Snippet || t==DocInclude::SnippetWithLines)
3820 {
3821 if (fileName == "this") fileName=parser()->context.fileName;
3822 parser()->tokenizer.setStateSnippet();
3823 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3824 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3825 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD))
3826 {
3827 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected block identifier, but found token %s instead while parsing the %s command",
3828 tok.to_string(),qPrint(saveCmdName));
3829 return;
3830 }
3831 blockId = "["+parser()->context.token->name+"]";
3832 }
3833
3834 children().append<DocInclude>(parser(),
3835 thisVariant(),
3836 fileName,
3837 localScope ? parser()->context.context : "",
3838 t,
3839 stripCodeComments,
3840 parser()->context.isExample,
3841 parser()->context.exampleName,
3842 blockId,isBlock,trimLeft);
3843 children().get_last<DocInclude>()->parse();
3844}

3846void DocPara::handleSection(char cmdChar,const QCString &cmdName)
3847{
3848 AUTO_TRACE("cmdName={}",cmdName);
3849 QCString saveCmdName = cmdName;
3850 // get the argument of the section command.
3851 Token tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3852 if (!tok.is(TokenRetval::TK_WHITESPACE))
3853 {
3854 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"expected whitespace after '%c%s' command",
3855 cmdChar,qPrint(saveCmdName));
3856 return;
3857 }
3858 tok=parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3859 if (tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
3860 {
3861 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected end of comment block while parsing the "
3862 "argument of command '%c%s'", cmdChar,qPrint(saveCmdName));
3863 return;
3864 }
3865 else if (!tok.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_WORD,TokenRetval::TK_LNKWORD))
3866 {
3867 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"unexpected token %s as the argument of '%c%s'",
3868 tok.to_string(),cmdChar,qPrint(saveCmdName));
3869 return;
3870 }
3871 parser()->context.token->sectionId = parser()->context.token->name;
3872 parser()->tokenizer.setStateSkipTitle();
3873 parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3874 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3875}

3885// For XML tags whose content is stored in attributes rather than
3886// contained within the element, we need a way to inject the attribute
3887// text into the current paragraph.
3888bool DocPara::injectToken(Token tok,const QCString &tokText)
3889{
3890 AUTO_TRACE();
3891 parser()->context.token->name = tokText;
3892 return parser()->defaultHandleToken(thisVariant(),tok,children());

3894
3895Token DocPara::handleStartCode()
3896{
3897 AUTO_TRACE();
3898 Token retval = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
3899 QCString lang = parser()->context.token->name;
3900 if (!lang.isEmpty() && lang.at(0)!='.')
3901 {
3902 lang="."+lang;
3903 }
3904 if (parser()->context.xmlComment)
3905 {
3906 parser()->context.token->verb = substitute(substitute(parser()->context.token->verb,"&lt;","<"),"&gt;",">");
3907 }
3908 // search for the first non-whitespace line, index is stored in li
3909 size_t i=0,li=0,l=parser()->context.token->verb.length();
3910 while (i<l && (parser()->context.token->verb.at(i)==' ' || parser()->context.token->verb.at(i)=='\n'))
3911 {
3912 if (parser()->context.token->verb.at(i)=='\n') li=i+1;
3913 i++;
3914 }
3915 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant(),
3916 parser()->context.context,
3917 stripIndentation(parser()->context.token->verb.mid(li)),
3918 DocVerbatim::Code,
3919 parser()->context.isExample,
3920 parser()->context.exampleName,
3921 FALSE,lang);
3922 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
3923 {
3924 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"code section ended without end marker");
3925 }
3926 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
3927 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("retval={}",retval.to_string());
3928 return retval;
3929}
3930
3931void DocPara::handleInheritDoc()
3932{
3933 if (parser()->context.memberDef) // inheriting docs from a member
3934 {
3935 const MemberDef *reMd = parser()->context.memberDef->reimplements();
3936 if (reMd) // member from which was inherited.
3937 {
3938 const MemberDef *thisMd = parser()->context.memberDef;
3939 //printf("{InheritDocs:%s=>%s}\n",qPrint(parser()->context.memberDef->qualifiedName()),qPrint(reMd->qualifiedName()));
3940 parser()->pushContext();
3941 parser()->context.scope=reMd->getOuterScope();
3942 if (parser()->context.scope!=Doxygen::globalScope)
3943 {
3944 parser()->context.context=parser()->context.scope->name();
3945 }
3946 parser()->context.memberDef=reMd;
3947 while (!parser()->context.styleStack.empty()) parser()->context.styleStack.pop();
3948 while (!parser()->context.nodeStack.empty()) parser()->context.nodeStack.pop();
3949 parser()->context.copyStack.push_back(reMd);
3950 parser()->internalValidatingParseDoc(thisVariant(),children(),reMd->briefDescription());
3951 parser()->internalValidatingParseDoc(thisVariant(),children(),reMd->documentation());
3952 parser()->context.copyStack.pop_back();
3953 auto hasParamCommand = parser()->context.hasParamCommand;
3954 auto hasReturnCommand = parser()->context.hasReturnCommand;
3955 auto retvalsFound = parser()->context.retvalsFound;
3956 auto paramsFound = parser()->context.paramsFound;
3957 parser()->popContext();
3958 parser()->context.hasParamCommand = hasParamCommand;
3959 parser()->context.hasReturnCommand = hasReturnCommand;
3960 parser()->context.retvalsFound = retvalsFound;
3961 parser()->context.paramsFound = paramsFound;
3962 parser()->context.memberDef = thisMd;
3963 }
3964 }
3965}
3966
3967
3968Token DocPara::handleCommand(char cmdChar, const QCString &cmdName)
3969{
3970 AUTO_TRACE("cmdName={}",cmdName);
3971 Token retval = Token::make_RetVal_OK();
3972 CommandType cmdId = Mappers::cmdMapper->map(cmdName);
3973 switch (cmdId)
3974 {
3975 case CommandType::UNKNOWN:
3976 {
3977 std::string str{cmdChar};
3978 children().append<DocWord>(parser(),thisVariant(),str.c_str() + cmdName);
3979 if (isAliasCmd(cmdName.view()))
3980 {
3981 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Found unexpanded alias '%c%s'. Check if number of arguments passed is correct.",cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3982 }
3983 else
3984 {
3985 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"Found unknown command '%c%s'",cmdChar,qPrint(cmdName));
3986 }
3987 }
3988 break;
3989 case CommandType::CMD_EMPHASIS:
3990 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Italic,cmdName,TRUE);
3991 retval=parser()->handleStyleArgument(thisVariant(),children(),cmdName);
3992 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Italic,cmdName,FALSE);
3993 if (!retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD)) children().append<DocWhiteSpace>(parser(),thisVariant()," ");
3994 break;
3995 case CommandType::CMD_BOLD:
3996 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Bold,cmdName,TRUE);
3997 retval=parser()->handleStyleArgument(thisVariant(),children(),cmdName);
3998 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Bold,cmdName,FALSE);
3999 if (!retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD)) children().append<DocWhiteSpace>(parser(),thisVariant()," ");
4000 break;
4001 case CommandType::CMD_CODE:
4002 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Code,cmdName,TRUE);
4003 retval=parser()->handleStyleArgument(thisVariant(),children(),cmdName);
4004 children().append<DocStyleChange>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.nodeStack.size(),DocStyleChange::Code,cmdName,FALSE);
4005 if (!retval.is(TokenRetval::TK_WORD)) children().append<DocWhiteSpace>(parser(),thisVariant()," ");
4006 break;
4007 case CommandType::CMD_BSLASH:
4008 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_BSlash);
4009 break;
4010 case CommandType::CMD_AT:
4011 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_At);
4012 break;
4013 case CommandType::CMD_LESS:
4014 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Less);
4015 break;
4016 case CommandType::CMD_GREATER:
4017 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Greater);
4018 break;
4019 case CommandType::CMD_AMP:
4020 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Amp);
4021 break;
4022 case CommandType::CMD_DOLLAR:
4023 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Dollar);
4024 break;
4025 case CommandType::CMD_HASH:
4026 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Hash);
4027 break;
4028 case CommandType::CMD_PIPE:
4029 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Pipe);
4030 break;
4031 case CommandType::CMD_DCOLON:
4032 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_DoubleColon);
4033 break;
4034 case CommandType::CMD_PERCENT:
4035 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Percent);
4036 break;
4037 case CommandType::CMD_NDASH:
4038 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Minus);
4039 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Minus);
4040 break;
4041 case CommandType::CMD_MDASH:
4042 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Minus);
4043 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Minus);
4044 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Minus);
4045 break;
4046 case CommandType::CMD_QUOTE:
4047 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Quot);
4048 break;
4049 case CommandType::CMD_PUNT:
4050 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Dot);
4051 break;
4052 case CommandType::CMD_PLUS:
4053 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Plus);
4054 break;
4055 case CommandType::CMD_MINUS:
4056 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Minus);
4057 break;
4058 case CommandType::CMD_EQUAL:
4059 children().append<DocSymbol>(parser(),thisVariant(),HtmlEntityMapper::Sym_Equal);
4060 break;
4061 case CommandType::CMD_SA:

4064 parser()->context.inSeeBlock=FALSE;
4065 break;
4066 case CommandType::CMD_RETURN:

4069 break;
4070 case CommandType::CMD_AUTHOR:

4072 break;
4073 case CommandType::CMD_AUTHORS:

4075 break;
4076 case CommandType::CMD_VERSION:

4078 break;
4079 case CommandType::CMD_SINCE:
4080 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Since);
4081 break;
4082 case CommandType::CMD_DATE:
4083 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Date);
4084 break;
4085 case CommandType::CMD_NOTE:
4086 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Note);
4087 break;
4088 case CommandType::CMD_WARNING:
4089 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Warning);
4090 break;
4091 case CommandType::CMD_PRE:
4092 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Pre);
4093 break;
4094 case CommandType::CMD_POST:
4095 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Post);
4096 break;
4097 case CommandType::CMD_COPYRIGHT:
4098 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Copyright);
4099 break;
4100 case CommandType::CMD_INVARIANT:
4101 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Invar);
4102 break;
4103 case CommandType::CMD_REMARK:
4104 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Remark);
4105 break;
4106 case CommandType::CMD_ATTENTION:
4107 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Attention);
4108 break;
4109 case CommandType::CMD_IMPORTANT:
4110 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::Important);
4111 break;
4112 case CommandType::CMD_PAR:
4113 retval = handleSimpleSection(DocSimpleSect::User);
4114 break;
4115 case CommandType::CMD_LI:
4116 {

4119 }
4120 break;
4121 case CommandType::CMD_SECTION:

4125 }
4126 break;
4127 case CommandType::CMD_SUBSECTION:

4154 retval = Token::make_RetVal_SubSubParagraph();
4155 }
4156 break;
4157 case CommandType::CMD_ISTARTCODE:

4161 }
4162 break;
4163 case CommandType::CMD_STARTCODE:

4166 retval = handleStartCode();

4168 break;
4169 case CommandType::CMD_HTMLONLY:
4170 {

4172 retval = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
4173 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.context,parser()->context.token->verb,DocVerbatim::HtmlOnly,parser()->context.isExample,parser()->context.exampleName,parser()->context.token->name=="block");
4174 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
4175 {
4176 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"htmlonly section ended without end marker");
4177 }
4178 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
4179 }
4180 break;
4181 case CommandType::CMD_MANONLY:
4182 {
4183 parser()->tokenizer.setStateManOnly();
4184 retval = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
4185 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.context,parser()->context.token->verb,DocVerbatim::ManOnly,parser()->context.isExample,parser()->context.exampleName);
4186 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
4187 {
4188 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"manonly section ended without end marker");

4191 }

4197 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.context,parser()->context.token->verb,DocVerbatim::RtfOnly,parser()->context.isExample,parser()->context.exampleName);

4209 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.context,parser()->context.token->verb,DocVerbatim::LatexOnly,parser()->context.isExample,parser()->context.exampleName);
4210 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
4211 {

4220 retval = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
4221 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.context,parser()->context.token->verb,DocVerbatim::XmlOnly,parser()->context.isExample,parser()->context.exampleName);
4222 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
4223 {
4224 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"xmlonly section ended without end marker");
4225 }
4226 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
4227 }
4228 break;
4229 case CommandType::CMD_DBONLY:
4230 {
4231 parser()->tokenizer.setStateDbOnly();
4232 retval = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
4233 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.context,parser()->context.token->verb,DocVerbatim::DocbookOnly,parser()->context.isExample,parser()->context.exampleName);
4234 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))

4237 }

4239 }
4240 break;
4241 case CommandType::CMD_ILITERAL:
4242 {
4243 DocVerbatim::Type t = DocVerbatim::JavaDocLiteral;
4244 parser()->tokenizer.setStateILiteralOpt();
4245 parser()->tokenizer.lex();
4246
4247 QCString fullMatch = parser()->context.token->verb;
4248 int idx = fullMatch.find('{');
4249 int idxEnd = fullMatch.find("}",idx+1);
4250 StringVector optList;
4251 if (idx != -1) // options present
4252 {
4253 QCString optStr = fullMatch.mid(idx+1,idxEnd-idx-1).stripWhiteSpace();
4254 optList = split(optStr.str(),",");
4255 for (const auto &opt : optList)
4256 {
4257 if (opt.empty()) continue;
4258 QCString locOpt(opt);
4259 locOpt = locOpt.stripWhiteSpace().lower();
4260 if (locOpt == "code")
4261 {
4262 t = DocVerbatim::JavaDocCode;
4263 }
4264 else if (!locOpt.isEmpty())
4265 {
4266 warn(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(), "Unknown option '%s' for '\\iliteral'",qPrint(opt));
4267 }
4268 }
4269 }
4270
4271 parser()->tokenizer.setStateILiteral();
4272 retval = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
4273 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.context,parser()->context.token->verb,t,parser()->context.isExample,parser()->context.exampleName);
4274 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
4275 {
4276 if (t == DocVerbatim::JavaDocCode)
4277 {
4278 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"javadoc code section ended without end marker");
4279 }
4280 else
4281 {
4282 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"javadoc literal section ended without end marker");
4283 }
4284 }
4285 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
4286 }
4287 break;
4288 case CommandType::CMD_IVERBATIM:
4289 case CommandType::CMD_VERBATIM:
4290 {
4291 if (cmdId == CommandType::CMD_VERBATIM)
4292 {
4293 parser()->tokenizer.setStateVerbatim();
4294 }
4295 else
4296 {
4297 parser()->tokenizer.setStateIVerbatim();
4298 }
4299 retval = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
4300 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant(),parser()->context.context,parser()->context.token->verb,DocVerbatim::Verbatim,parser()->context.isExample,parser()->context.exampleName);
4301 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
4302 {
4303 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"verbatim section ended without end marker");
4304 }
4305 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
4306 }
4307 break;
4308 case CommandType::CMD_DOT:
4309 {
4310 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant(),
4311 parser()->context.context,

4316 DocVerbatim *dv = children().get_last<DocVerbatim>();
4317 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
4318 QCString width,height;

4320 parser()->tokenizer.setStateDot();
4321 retval = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
4322 dv->setText(parser()->context.token->verb);
4323 dv->setWidth(width);
4324 dv->setHeight(height);
4325 dv->setLocation(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr());
4326 if (!Config_getBool(HAVE_DOT))
4327 {
4328 warn_doc_error(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr(),"ignoring \\dot command because HAVE_DOT is not set");
4329 children().pop_back();

4334 }

4336 }

4338 case CommandType::CMD_MSC:
4339 {
4340 children().append<DocVerbatim>(parser(),thisVariant(),
4341 parser()->context.context,
4342 parser()->context.token->verb,
4343 DocVerbatim::Msc,
4344 parser()->context.isExample,
4345 parser()->context.exampleName);
4346 DocVerbatim *dv = children().get_last<DocVerbatim>();
4347 parser()->tokenizer.setStatePara();
4348 QCString width,height;
4349 parser()->defaultHandleTitleAndSize(CommandType::CMD_MSC,&children().back(),dv->children(),width,height);
4350 parser()->tokenizer.setStateMsc();
4351 retval = parser()->tokenizer.lex();
4352 dv->setText(parser()->context.token->verb);
4353 dv->setWidth(width);
4354 dv->setHeight(height);
4355 dv->setLocation(parser()->context.fileName,parser()->tokenizer.getLineNr());
4356 if (retval.is_any_of(TokenRetval::TK_NONE,TokenRetval::TK_EOF))
